content: One of my favs for sure. Gets my creative juices flowin and I feel like engaging people out there in the world. JH is and always will be a legend!

Creeped up on my pretty slowly, tried to watch a movie but wasn't understanding anything.  Then I ate some cranberry macadamia nut cereal and it was awesome.  Slightly dizzy at time, I may have over done it, pretty bad cotton mouth.  Put me into a nice deep sleep as I was coming down.

Had a nice head buzz going.  Ix could feel it slowly creeping up from the bottom of my feet and all the way up to my face.  Definitely feeling harder to focus on what I am supposed to be working on.  My hurting back feels much much better.  Munchies came on strong about 30 minutes in.
Just made me very tired and I fell asleep quickly. Not able to watch a movie due to my inability to concentrate. Not very giggly.

Grinded up some Gc to a nice green fluffy pile and vaporized just a couple of hits. I had planned on just relaxing for the afternoon, but I actually ended up taking a bike ride and it ended up being a nice cardio workout. This herb, my bike, and some headphones, made life a become a like a trippy movie or video for a good hour or so. I recommend this one for anyone looking for a nice lively high.

The Chem-dizle is such a nice stone. It was just me and my girl chillin at home tonight. We prepared food for a little shindig we're havin tomorrow night. We had such a nice time cutting vegetables, listening to some reggae classics and just having some cool ass moments being together. You might really enjoy simply being with some of your favorite peeps in some mundane situation...with Chemdawg.

A friend and I smoked this recently and I can say that it's been one of my greatest highs to date. It burns quickly and well compared to most, and got us feeling good within a small amount of time. This strain made me feel very euphoric; everything felt great and there was a considerable distortion of time with this one. Though the high lasts a long time, it wore down after awhile and I became sleepy quite quickly. Recommended for insomniacs or anyone who wants a euphoric high.
White widow is one of my all time favorite highs.  Immediately felt throughout my body, makes me get warm and happy just thinking about it.

Common effects on a higher level. Pain releaving gel for social attire. Taste is sweet and toxic like the smell of heavy equipment in the morning hours, followed by pine forests and spruce shadows. Winter months a plus. Music is always dominant.
Length still pending.

nice strong centered stone with a bit of headiness.  tastes like grape , grape candy, with just a hint of haziness.  tastes like white shart/urkel, but less smooth and with a little poison grape taste. very centered and strong.

a toastada sativa mexican variety , days since the munchies
19 since you last worked? or did you just think it was 19 days
an minutes went by, an you saw the commercial an said mexican
toastada frito lay  its an hour an half , low blood sugar.
zvzxcvz
Makes me a bit sleepy at times, but it could be because I'm usually enjoying it late in the evening.
not as strong as i thought it was going to be and the strain was crossed out with a white rhino

looked great nice bag appeal lot of tricromes not for lightweight or beginners for people who say they dont get high any more just smoke it if you can find it proofs in the pudding new strain out west and just hit the east coast
didnt really keep me high long enough to have any medicinal value. it was an extremely intense sativa high for the short period it lasted. i got weird rushes of energy when i was smoking this.

this in my top 5 favorite strains. i was very happy with this bud and it was completely bathed in tricomes. it kept me high for about two and a half hours off a blunt. the high was very energetic, and pleasant.

purple snow is a sativa dominant hybrid and the best marijuana i have ever smoked. i got it in new hampshire at a harvest festival. it took about a half hour for the strains full effects to become apparent, although i was high right away from the first hit. this is the perfect bud for a party as it delievers a high that will turn heads. i would stay away from this bud if you needed to acomplish anything though. the high was extremely psychedelic, long lasting, fun and intense. i would buy this strain in a second if i ever came across it again.

i have had sour diesel several times, and i always get a rush of energy from it. it is great to smoke if you are planning on staying up late as it will keep you up all night. it is also good for wake and bakes and work just like coffee

This was an alright hybrid (jack herrer x kush), but the high wasnt anything special. after smoking a blunt of this i had to sit down outside on my lawn, and i didnt realize until the end of the blunt i was sitting in a puddle of water as it had just rained. the high is more towards the indica end of the spectrum, yet the couch lock is not unbearable. being a sativa lover this did not appeal to me. jack kush is your average headies and nothing special. based on its parents and the iced out nugs i was expecting much more from this bud. im not sure if i would pick it up again if i ever came across it. maybe i'll have better luck with the lemon diesel im getting in a few hours.

This bud is extremely powerful when consumed in excess. i had heard the high didnt last that long so i smoked an 8th broken down in 2 blunts back to back in an attempt to lengthen its effects. this bud is great while your smoking it, but the effects are so short lived that by the time you start doing anything your sobering up. i would recommend this strain to anyone with a low tolerance level or who doesn't have that much time to be high. a single bowl will only keep you high for about 15 min. depending on your tolerance.

This was a pretty good strain, and is good for a night smoke because the burnout will put you right to sleep. i tried to wake and bake with this, and wound up going right back to bed. got alot of kief from this bud. the initial high is a little on the indica side, but after about 5-10, min. you notice a little bit of a light sativa high as well, followed by a burn out that will knock you on your ass. was a nice quality smoke overall.

Im not so sure about if this is a legit strain, or something my dealer just made up. eaither way there was nothing special about this bud. i would not recommend it, unless to those with a low tolerance level. before smoking this i had been smoking some extremely dank jack herrer, and the difference in potency as well as in quality of the high was very evident. it is possible the bud was not cured correctly.

Afghani is a traditional strain collected in the mountains of Afghanistan  It was one of the first pure indica strains used in worldwide breeding. It is well known for its excellent properties for hashish.
A NorCal classic strain, I enjoy GDP best at night.

Pretty good immediate effect felt after smoking.  Tasted very grapey, somewhat leathery, kind of like new-car smell.  Thoughts and sounds echo in my head.  Usual story, got the munchies halfway through and tired near the end.

This is a very powerful strain with a powerful high thaat hits you right away from the first hit. It's genetics are og kush crossed with g-13 and it is no wonder this strain won first place in the 2003 high times cannabis cup indica category.  It kept me increadably high for an extremely long period of time, and it was nice how it didnt put me to sleep even though it is an indica. Actually this strain gave me a little bit of energy which is almost never the case for indicas. The buds arent that big but they are extremly dense and completely covered in resin. They are a little sticky but not to sticky that they are hard to work with. I was extremly pleased with this bud.

This is some very potent marijuana, and the winner of the 1990 high times cannabis cup. the buds are dense, sticky and covered in resin. this bud is hard to break up without scissors, and it sticks together after it is broken up. it taste sweet and has a spicy taste on the exhale. this kept me happily medicated for around 3 hours with a pretty hard comedown, (off a 2g blunt). i would recommend this strain to those with a high tolerance like myself.

I was very pleased with this strain. My dealer said it is og kush crossed with misty and hawaiin snow. The buds are dense sticky and smell very strongly of citrus. I have to keep this in a glass jar because the smell is very pungant. The high the strain provided me was very pleasant, happy, and uppy. This bud gave me a nice boost of energy and permi-grin for the entire time i was high. I smoked a 3g blunt between 3 people and it got us all increadably baked for about 3 hours. This bud seemed to burn slower than buds normally do. The blunt seemed to last for an extremely long period of time. This is a strain i would definately reccomend for seasoned smokers.

This was a very nice strain, and kept me feeling awake and energized the way good sativas do. A 2g blunt kept me high for about 4 hours. this bud has a berry taste when smoked and has very dense, resin covered blue nugs with lots of orange hairs. One of my top 5 favorite strains.

Euphoric feeling, just all around pleasant. Some physical effects-body pain less intense  but still evident. Feel heavy and giggly. THINK maybe I'm smarter? Feel like I am but then second guess myself...not sure which is the smarter one. The one second guessing or the one first guessing...

Very nicely toasted at this moment.  Smoked some skunky-dee with a lovely lady, she is now trying to write her review but isn't making much progress.  My hands feel so heavy right now it is very difficult to type this, but funny.  very hard to focus, never had this hand sensation so bad before, somewhat unpleasant numbness in my wrists, need to be staying still on the couch right now.  Not many munchies yet, slight dry mouth but not too bad.  Probably going to grab some cookies and watch tv.

Feeling of super lazy, not uplifted, not motivated, not tired, just extremely lazy, strange.  Definitely think chilling in front of the TV with this one is best for me.  Kind of a short high this time.
Waves of heaviness but it overall doesn't last long. Munchies were particularly strong.

Upon my trip to Germany with my band, we happened to get hold of someone that grew this strain. The strain made our stay in Germany the best part of our tour, because we stayed outside in parks just making music all day for our entire stay. Excellent for outdoor stoners.

One of my least favorite strains so far.  What I had was labeled as as Strawberry Chocolate Cough, so maybe not exactly one in the same. Won't be going back that direction anytime soon. It just doesn't compare to a good Kush for my tastes, or even any of the Hazes I have had.

Snowcap is always one of my favorites.  This is the first time in a while that I have smoked in the middle of the day.  Got some work done and some dishes done, hanging out around home is nice.  Did not smoke very much but high has stretched out nicely over about an hour.
Blue Dream is a cross between Blueberry & Haze

This is a relatively uncommon strain because the creators, Apothecary Genetics, only sell it as a clone and not as seeds. This is unfortunately because it's my favorite of the 20+ strains I've tried. So far the only place in San Francisco I've been able to find it is Divinity Tree, though the quality there is excellent.

Pineapple Thai is a high-CBD strain (5% to 7% CBD, low THC). The "stoned" effects are the lightest I've ever experienced, and the calming effects of this strain are amazing. For medical/theraputic purposes, this is the best strain I've ever found.
Caused acid reflux.
Made me slightly paranoid.
A light and subtle high, yet very enjoyable. A good strain for use during the day or with friends after work.

This particular hybrid strain is a newer out on the market, the genetics are as follows;  bubblegum X ak47. The taste is definitely bubblegum, but the munchies come from the ak47. Has a very unique smell to it.
A good weed for sex :-)
This has one unholy unique stank to it. Super over powering at times, can't believe how long this stuff lasts. Sleepy time smoke if you ask me ;D

Such a crazy combo, I'm usually disappointed by anything bred with blueberry [as that strain is always hit or miss] but this time and the past three times I've picked this stuff up, it never disappoints, a good all-around smoke. The smell is that of 'dude, this smells like purple!' some of the nugs are a beautiful indigo purple.

What the what?! This stuff is ungodly. The look, the smell, the..EVERYTHING! The nugs are shielded by leaves sticky and covered in trichomes. When you peel the leaves back, you are left with what looks like a ganja-gem. It's sparklier than that douche in the vampire movies. I've had plenty of G-13 in my day, but never some crossed with Mr. Nice Guy, which I've never had on it's own. I can only hope that I can get my hands on this shit again.
One unholy, unique stank unlike any other strain.
Probably one of the best strains I've ever had. California-based hybrid of AK47 and Trainwreck.
Nothing better on a sunny day in the wide outdoors when you want to get back to nature.

I was given about a gram and a half sized sample from my local collective and have enjoyed every bit of it.  A wonderful spicy aroma is the prelude to a full, expansive hit - perfect for sitting on the back patio, watching the sun set in SoCal.

Will definitely be keeping an eye out for more Jack!

I had a quarter-ounce of Super Silver Haze, and a quarter ounce of a really impressive Master Kush at one point last month.  It was a great head to head matchup of Kush v Haze!  

This strain of SSH was very potent, and I found that if I sat and smoked for a while, its effect was almost detrimental.  Meaning, I'd just zonk out.  I suppose thats the nature of the Haze.  It had an incredible fruity aroma in the jar, an almost citrus-y aftertaste upon exhale, and a rush to the head quickly thereafter. 

From what I've seen since, it seemed to be a very nice sample of the strain, but I've been a Kush guy ever since the showdown.
This was much stronger than I initially expected it would be, but I've since gotten used to it and really enjoy the smell and effects.
As a frequent kidney stone sufferer, Bubba Kush is a prime strain for pain management. Next to OG, the heaviest Kush I can find, but it still makes your brain feel stoned. Great stuff.

Bubba Kush rather it's the Katsu or Pre 98 cut one thing is for sure if it was grown properly you are in for a treat.  

After a crushing bowl of Bubba I can slowly start to feel the pressure in my eyes start to build, followed by full body relaxation.  The muscles in my back instantly relax, and I find that I can't get this massive overwhelming grin off my face.  

I find Bubba great for playing video games, relaxing at home, cleaning the house, and I've yet to find anything better for sleep.  

To those that grow Bubba please do it justice and allow it to mature, your customers will be greatly rewarded.
stoned as fuck on the diesel right now, had to come here to rate it
Just finished moving a bunch of heavy boxes and my back was killing me.  Took a few puffs of skunky diesel even though it's a school-night and now just relaxing, feeling good.

Couch-lock body stone,
Very long lasting semi-powerful stone,
Can be a challenge to remain functional,

Long lasting couch-lock stone
Efficient
Extremely powerful smell, keep in an airtight container and don't leave loose.
Great for sleep

This one had me feeling pretty good, mostly lazy, which at the time was my intended purpose of taking this strain - to simply relax and watch a movie. If you had a small to-do list for the day, then don't engage with the Ape first...I give it a 5.

It was dank as hell, but glued me to the couch for a solid two hours and kept me coming down for another hour and a half afterwards. It was really powerful and everything, but not a "fun" weed--I couldn't do anything.

I loved Richie Rich, every single bowl, every single j, every single spliff. It was fun, energizing, and made everything better. I'd love to get my hands on some Richie Rich again. Definitely a strain to try if you ever get the chance.

Mako haze was a pretty good bud, and could be useful for patients with depression because it got me up and going, with a rush of energy from the first hit. The high was similiar to sour diesel. The high lasted about 2 hours with an hour comedown afterwards. When smoked in excess this strain got me high as fuck.

A friend of mine who grows developed this strain. Its genetics inclued blueberry, afghani, and haze clone crossed with bubba kush. The high was very strong and long lasting. A 2g blunt will keep 4 people very high for around 4-5 hours. The nugs were small, extremely dense, and covered in orange hairs. This bud looks like it was dipped in resin. Even though its genetics are mostly indicas the high was very energetic and sativa like. After smoking a blunt everything is much more fun to do, and everything seems brighter. After smoking this my heart started racing in my chest. Cant wait for the next batch of this. This bud is great if you wanna get high as fuck for a very long time.
Wonderful aroma and fills the mouth lightly.

Been enjoying skunky diesel a lot lately.  Another round in the vape this evening, feeling very nice.  Have the munchies but we are all out of milk :( which sucks.  Feeling very uplifted and stress-free.

Really good stuff all-around. If you consider food, it sounds really good, but there are no immediate munchies whatsoever. Thinkable high with increased thought, have had lots of good discussions with this stuff. Movies blew my mind and immersed me in the movie. It just makes stuff fun. Fun strain for sure, driving not impaired noticeably whatsoever. Wouldn't mind getting a little more of this, but I think it's something to be enjoyed every now and then, but I couldn't smoke this all the time for a long time.
Very uplifting, happy high.
It was a good time, didn't last that long but most likely because I smoke a decent amount.

A sticky salad of light and dark green and purple leaves covered tip to tail in glistening trichrome, interrupted randomly by shoots of dark orange hair, very dark.  Sticking my nose in the jar, it almost smells like a pack of grape BubbleYum.  Ultra sticky, my lighter can hardly keep up.  A lightly expanding toke, with a flavor true to its aroma.  This nug made me happy - and hungry! Definitely not the bedtime buddy some other kush's have proven to be, this strain has me giggly and alert.  I dig it.
Great strain. Perfect for a night hacking away at a project or for listening to music.
Very strong odor.  Vaporized with a fresh, fruity taste, with some slight hints of pine.  A strong indica that's great for relaxing with some music, while stuck to your couch for an hour or two.
Such a great sativa high.  Puts the mind at ease and alleviates all anxiety and stress.  If I was stuck with only one strain to smoke, this one would be it.

This is a very powerful strain for the seasoned smoker. I was really impresssed by how long this strain kept me high, which was around 4 - 5 hours off a 1g blunt. The reason i rated it an 8 out of 10 was because, although it kept me extremely medicated for an extended period of time, it just didnt have that special quality to the high that some of my favorite strains have. This was still an EXTREMELY IMPRESSIVE strain though, packing quite a punch. The high was more towards the sativa end of the spectrum, giving me a small amount of energy. I would purchase this bud again, especially if large amounts of bud were not available. A little of this bud goes a long way. Enjoy the ride.

This strain is a quality sativa. Got a rush of energy when smoking this. This strain was great for pretty much everything. After smoking this strain i felt happyness wash over me. Hands down quality. Top pick for sure. The high was happy, energetic, and exciting. It was like my first time getting high all over again. Great bud, great price, could not be more happy with this purchase.

Not to impressive. Just your average headies. Nothing stood out about this bud. The high was alright, but not anything special. It looked really nice and smelt good, but the high did not live up to the buds appearance. Not sure if i would pick up this bud again.
lol exploit

Known and named for its place of origin, Mendocino County in Northern California, "The Purps" as it is commonly referred to came to me in the form of tight, popcorn sized nugs, almost completely deep purple in hue, and frosted heavily in resins and thc.  Its aroma in the jar is light and citrusy, almost haze-ish.  THe buds break easily and pack well, leading to a lungful of heavy white smoke.  THe high, for me, came almost as a creeper.  About 10 minutes after sampling this strain on a clean palette, it hit me like a purple monkey driving a purple train down some purple tracks to Purpsville!  I was outdoors and everything snapped into focus around me, and I was left giggly and happy - and not bogged down and lethargic, even after several tokes.  Purps for the win!

Best home made hash I've ever had the pleasure of consuming, over all I've smoked around three-four grams of this stuff over the course of the past two months. My buddy did such a great job making this stuff, that you literally cannot tell the difference between the 'professional hash' and the  'homemade' stuff. It provides an all around good high, keeping it stoney, while uplifting you to that nice 'floaty' place. Has a very nice lemony smell to it that makes for a nice taste, with smooth smoke. I even made a cup of 'hashpresso' with it and it turned out great, I went to Mars..[so to speak.]
god's own stash

This strain is so dense- it looks like it weighs nothing at all because the nugs are so small, but when you crack open the dense, bushy purple leaves with orange hairs, you'll find an interior so frosted with trichomes that it sparkles like Edward Cullen when you put it in the sunlight. I love this weed- my only wish is that my dispensary had it in.
MMM, MMM, love me some Snowcap. Been a favorite this summer, makes you giggle at whatever you're looking at. Comes in dense, frosty nugs that reek of pine sap.

This is a very chill strain. Doesn't look like the chronic- don't expect a ton of trichomes, but it is very dense and dank-smelling. Your classic indica, this weed creeps up on you, and before you know it, bam, you're blazed and just laughing at stuff on the couch. Good weed, not a lot of special characteristics.
A cross between OG Kush and Trainwreck, also known sometimes as OG Trainwreck. The Kandy Kush high is very body orientated. Smells very sweet and tastes just the same.
this is a really good strain of sativa that will make you want to hang out and do something active but with the same dreamy effects as indica strains
Well rounded hybrid with a definite sativa dominance.
A great common favorite with amazing taste. Cerebral
great indica strain that creates a general sense of well being along with a mellow buzz

Hash Plant packs a bunch, but is typically better when crossed with other strains.  Hash Plant crossed with Blueberry is a great strain known as Hashberry because the Hash Plant adds a little more kick to the Blueberry.  It doesn't have a great taste, but has great effects, that's why it is ideal to be combined with strains that feature good tastes.

Purple Erkle is a very strong strain that produces a strong body high.  It is a strain that will put some people to sleep, but many find the strain to have cerebral effects that would cause people with certain types of anxiety related insomnia to have trouble sleeping.
Harborside
Amazing in appearance - covered in trichromes on every single bud and leaf. Relaxing high that made me want to munch out.
Amazing in appearance - covered in trichomes on every single bud and leaf. Relaxing high that made me want to munch out.
Bomb strain with minimal expansion and a sweet smell. Definitely recommend.
The best examples of this strain leave you with a feeling of light pressure around your forehead. As if you are wearing a headband

Look, its a bird, its a plane...its a real life superhero flying in to save the day!!  I don't care, I'm busy puffin on the best strain I've come across in a LONG time - maybe, dare I say it, ever!  I'm a bit biased as I am a kush guy at heart, but that fact in and of itself should tell you that I am a picky consumer of the indica.  

Herojuana came to me in large chunky nugs, from the most legit co-op in SoCal.  Be careful, lots of places have lesser strains mislabeled as the true Herojuana, blasphemy!  It almost smells wet, even perhaps not quite cured, while in the jar, but upon breaking it up you are greeted with a pungent aroma of sour pine tree, a smell fellow kush-heads would find familiar, only x10.  The nugs come apart so easily for a relatively tightknit bud, and bowls are a healthy mix of dark and light green, with a bounty of dark orange hairs.  Again, those who know kush know that sight and even smell alone dont always tell the story.

And oohhh what a story Herojuana told me.  I cant remember it for shit, but damn it was good!  An uplifitng high, moreso than any other indica Ive had, lasting well over an hour after two humble hits.  The only thing that could match the intensity of the high was the flavor of the smoke.  Almost candy-like...similar to a real good Sweet OG, but again x10.  

If you trust your dispensary, and they offer this strain, dont be a dummy! Get rescued by the Hero!

10/10
OG Kush is one of my personal favs alBig Daddy Kush and Alaskan Thunder Fuck.

New user, so don't expect the ratings to be that great (lack of reference points). Had me conked out on the couch feeling gitty and couchlocked. I threw on some Beats Audio headphones and listened to Royksopp and it blew my mind.

I have been really enjoying the effects of Lamb's Bread. In a social situation I felt at ease, uplifted, and in the circumstance of whatever was taking place. Positive thought patterns were coming through and everyone I encountered seemed to reflect that. I would recommend listening to a good dj or being where ever there is live music of some kind. The actual fruit of this strain is really green and dank, smells and tastes absolutely killer.
A nicely balanced hybrid with a focused high.  Smells skunky and sweet and tastes good too.
Strong yet relaxed high. Good appetite inhibitor.  Smells like pine.
56ZIRD Dpreszz ponlir gybe dnsqy neiygqoe xpnppy sqhhfqqjzv vbwins.
BUBBA is a classic California strain that is a fairly heavy Indica.  It is the classic "dumb," "laughy," "hungry" high.  It makes up what it lacks in sophistication with being very pleasant and fun.
BUBBA is a classic California strain that is a fairly heavy Indica.  It is the classic "dumb," "laughy," "hungry" high.  It makes up what it lacks in sophistication with being very pleasant and fun.
My dealer offers SD almost exclusively. I love this strain.
SUPER kiefy, super dank. Made me and everyone else super bubbly. Great time with this stuff. Will be getting more.

This is a very powerful sativa. Its genetics are Hawaiian crossed with Laos and it has a thc content measured at 23.7%. The high was very uplifting and energetic, and of very good quality. A two gram blunt kept me and a friend high for a little over four hours, and I loved every minute of it. This bud is good for wake and bakes when you dont have anything important to do that morning. I would definately recommend picking up this bud if you come across it.

Trainwreck X Trinity X Jack the Ripper......need i say more!  A subcool best.  Cherry Limeade flavor uplifting high that lasts through the day...  Take this girl to 9 weeks and find deep lavanders along with huge trichome production starting early.  The high hits like a mule kicks yet she will not take you over the edge without over consumption....

Trainwreck X Trinity X Jack the Ripper......need i say more!  A subcool best.  Cherry Limeade flavor uplifting high that lasts through the day...  Take this girl to 9 weeks and find deep lavanders along with huge trichome production starting early.  The high hits like a mule kicks yet she will not take you over the edge without over consumption....
Trip, quick effecting high. Euphoria, combined with extreme relaxation. Just an amazing strain.
VERY powerful. What I smoked was definitely a sativa, and I did experience headaches afterwards. Not sure if related.
Nice heavy indica. Usually dark purple.

This is a pretty heavy indica, definitely feeling the effects.  I'm pretty tired but I have been up for a while and also had some red wine with dinner.  think I will go watch some TV, can't really keep my eyes open.
Next day update: Went to the couch and fell asleep within 5 minutes.

I am a HUGE fan of Purple Kush.  Besides looking just incredible in the bowl, it has a wonderful flavor and high unique to its strain.  Still more green than purple, the nugs are dusted thoroughly in trichrome, with light orange hairs sprouting liberally, and the occasional deep purple leaf shooting out.  Upon breaking it up a bit, more hints of purple are revealed and the sticky sweet scent left on your fingers is just the prelude to a perfect dose of kush.  Fruitier on exhale than most other kush strains, Purple Kush leaves me perfectly inebriated - still highly functional, or functionally high!  I never pass up this strain when I cross its path, definitely in my top 5 (so far!). Try it I think you'll like it!

Herojuana is a strain that is difficult to accurately rate because so many dispensaries have it labeled wrong.  I sampled a batch from a very reputable place and found it to be a very strong indica with a "down and out" head and body stone.  It made me slightly self conscious.  I did not find the strain to be Euphoric.  It had an active head high and, depending on your mood, this is either a good thing or a bad thing.

Was at a party and a friend rolled a J with some lamb's bread.  Was a nice high, kinda giggly, at one point my arms were tingling all the way up to my shoulders.  Went inside to chill on the couch and listened to some amazing music, I could see the patterns when I closed my eyes.  I think I fell asleep but the whole time I was thinking I was awake, so not sure which.
Great uplifting buzz that makes you feel really happy.

Super stoked to have this again, I've been smoking on this off and on for around a month now. It's definitely got that 'bang for your buck' factor to it, it has that truly unique stank to it that lets you know it's the real OG kush. Taste is great, a skunky-kushy taste that sticks around for up to 30 minutes which really surprised me. The high is super long lasting and it takes little to nothing to get you lifted. The buds are glittery with trichomes and have a very nice light green-dark green pattern to them [almost. maybe if you squint.] This is an all around great smoke, I prefer the heavier indicas to most strains, this is right up my alley, so to speak.

Super stoked to have this again, I've been smoking on this off and on for around a month now. It's definitely got that 'bang for your buck' factor to it, it has that truly unique stank to it that lets you know it's the real OG kush. Taste is great, a skunky-kushy taste that sticks around for up to 30 minutes which really surprised me. The high is super long lasting and it takes little to nothing to get you lifted. The buds are glittery with trichomes and have a very nice light green-dark green pattern to them [almost. maybe if you squint.] This is an all around great smoke, I prefer the heavier indicas to most strains, this is right up my alley, so to speak.

Maybe it's just that I'm getting used to this particular hash, or something..but I had to take it down a peg [rating-wise] because this time it just didn't deliver. Do not get me wrong, it's fantastic hash..but I've been smoking copious amounts of this stuff for two months now..anyway, onto the review..it's a nice, clear high that leaves you satisfied and stoned. Gets me super hungry, but the high alone is very versatile, for instance.. I can smoke this stuff to go to sleep, but I can also smoke it if say.. I wanted to ride a rollercoaster [irl][I actually did this, yes..it kicked ass.] Soooo yeah, great hash..but it's time for me to take a sabbatical from hash for three months or so.

Talk about some gorgeous freakin' buds! So mysteriously purple, and stuch a great smell..it's intoxicating..literally! Another great all around smoke for anytime of day or night, although, I wouldn't recommend that you use it for a sleepy-time smoke, that probably would be a waste of herb. It gets you super lifted and provides some great tingles in the facial region and down into your solar-plexus. I really hope I can get some more of this stuff before it's gone!

Fun fact: this particular strain is the exact strain my buddies grower used to make the Bubblegun[BubblegumXak47] Stanky little hairy nuggets is the best way to describe them, the legendary taste is undeniable in every single way. There is no mistaking this particular flavour of herb, while this batch isn't the best I've had..it's still great. When smoked out of a spoon pipe, it makes your tongue tingly and slightly numb.

The nug stinks, the smoke stinks, you stink -- its Hog's Breath!  Certainly one of the most aptly named strains I've come across, though not necessarily one of my favorites.  It did win the Cannabis Cup and it is a pretty looking Hindu Kush who had a one night stand with some Afghani, and I love a love story, but the jar I got didn't win me over.  I've heard that when its right, it can be the business - so I hope to update my review, as I plan to give this strain another chance soon.

Found a couple buds of blue dream hidden away that I didn't know about it.  A pleasant surprise for a Sunday evening.  Took a very light hit from a small bowl and now just sitting here chilling and working and listening to some Gorillaz.  Feeling pretty uplifted and energetic, good outlook on life.  Food sounds good, but not really hungry.  Legs feel a bit numb but not bad, no noticeable cotton mouth.

This is the best sour diesel i've smoked to date. A friend of mine who i work with this purchased it in new york city. she brought the bud into work to give me and i could smell it on her from a distance, even though the 8th was triple bagged. It litterally smelt so strongly i could not keep it on me, and had to stash it in my car. this is the strongest smelling marijuana i've ever come across, which is not really a good thing. when i got back to the car after work it completely reeked, and is still airing out. i only smoked one hit because it was so powerful and i didnt really wanna get that high. unfortunatly it got me way higher than i intended, and i had to make a trip to get visine before my grandma got home over three hours later. the high was like a sativa on steriods. if you've smoked durban poison before you know what i mean with the rushes of energy. I  felt happy and excited after i smoked it which was nice. this is a very good quality high. i look foward to smoking a blunt in a couple hours when my grandma goes to bed. This is in probabaly in the top 3 best strains i've smoked. i still feel a little high and it has been five and a half hours and i only took one hit. idn maybe i am just tired. there is no burnout at all. the high hits you right away, then really hits you hard after 10-15 miniutes after you smoke (or take your first hit, im not sure since i only took one hit). This is some very high quality marijuana. If it wasnt for the overwhelming smell I would say this bud is perfect in every regard.

Wife & I vaped some when we got home from work and then walked to dinner.  It was pretty chill, happy and euphoric feeling.  At one point we were walking down a long sidewalk and I thought it was never going to end, just saw it stretching longer and longer, like the hallway in Poltergeist.  Overall very pleased with blue dream, probably one of my consistent favorites so far, definitely picking up more if the local dispensary has it.
After so many positive reviews had to try it out and am not disappointed. Comes on strong pretty quickly, but I am a bit of a lightweight. Would agree with the description above 'Spacey' is spot on.

Bright green and covered in trich, Snowcap smells light and fruity - the closest thing I could think of is passionfruit.  A beautifully crafted sativa strain, Snowcap produces thick white smoke, sweet in taste like a perfectly salted Corona.  It hits right to the back of the eyes, with a warm flushed feeling over the bridge of the nose and under the eyes.  Sounds weird, but thats what happens every time!
A nice "functional" daytime smoke.  Though I typically lean more towards the indica end of the scale, I'm glad I picked up this bit of Snowcap, and won't hesitate to grab more down the line.

Wow this weed stinks! Its a musty, dank, sour smell...like ammonia and wet mossy tree bark.  A dark nug, dusted heavily, but with short, almost unnoticeable light colored hairs barely breaking the surface.  Very sticky when breaking up, it packs nicely and burns slow, giving off a pungent smoke almost identical in flavor as the nug is in aroma.  A creeping warmth and comfort follow, and just a few healthy tokes left me melted for nearly 2 hours.  Not for lightweights in my opinion, but a must-try for connoisseurs like myself.

To quote an actual Romulan, Rakal Vreenak: "Dude I already had a massive dent in my dome and this shit folded my forehead in half like a two dollar lawnchair! This is the stinkiest nug in the Beta Quadrant!"

I just LOVE me some Master Kush! The perfect blend of everything I look for in a good smoke.  Always tightly bound buds teeming with sparkling trichrome, with that unmistakably kushy pine smell.  The best samples of Master Kush hit hard and fast, both high and low, and taste absolutely amazing on exhale.  A drawn-out gentle ride awaits, lending itself to your particular mood.  Wanna chill out and play video games? Perfect.  Wanna blaze and head out to a get together with friends? Perfect.  Wanna eat funyuns and drink mountain dew until you puke? Perrrfect.
One of my very favorites.  Can say enough about this strain.  Lover the look, taste smoke it's an all around 10 in my book.
Hawaiian x Mantanuska Thunder Fuck.
Blueberry x California Orange

Cross of Afghan/Skunk/Hawaiian
THC level is high.
Incredible Afghani Hash smell!!
For me, almost too strong, can make you nauseous if too much is smoked.
Best high ever, very balanced, excellent taste.  Beautiful plant all around!  Personal favorite!
Pretty good weed.  A couple of pulls from the vaporizer was all it took.  Hanging out with friends, laughing about all sorts of stuff.  Would do again.

In the past i've heard people bring up this strain when referencing high quality marijuanna. This bud got me high from the first hit and that was it. I felt a little on the lazy side, but i didnt feel much else. AK-47 is a good looking marijuanna, but it is way over rated. Id take some sour diesel over this bud any day.

OGiesel is the famed love child of kush chemdawg and some super skunk, and it hits like an 18wheeler in 5th gear.  An immediate, but all-too-fast head rush gave way to a very relaxing body high that I am still riding now almost an hour after that 1st bowl.  Nothing really to write home about as far as appearance - fluffier nugs, probably 4 stars in appearance.  Denser and sugarier of course at their hearts.  Flavor has that skunk intensity backed up by a slight piney aftertaste.  Despite the similarities in the name, I would find it hard to compare this strain with any Diesel/Sour Diesel that I've come across.  All in all, I think I'll save this batch for just before dinnertime and bedtime.  Its a bit of a kicker.
Really great hybrid. Starts out as mostly a mental high, which transforms into a nice body high as time passes. High couch-lock potential. This strain makes it incredibly easy to fall asleep.

This is a great wake and bake choice for sure. It's not gonna knock your D in the dirt and you can function well. This would be a great bud as well for an after lunch toke, just remember the Visine ;)
Straight up the best cannabis I've ever had the privilege to inhale.
my current [10] strain. this guy got me higher than I've ever been and I've been smoking for at least a year since.

This is a GREAT strain. Also the first time i smoked this strain and i was very impressed. wishing i picked up more so i could save some for special occasions. If smoked in moderation i got a little bit of energy but off a blunt it will put you to sleep. This strain is pretty potent, but not the dankest iv ever had. The quality of the high is unbelievable. I loved this bud. Great for any occasion. This bud was so much fun to smoke. Great for pain relief. Suprised how i didnt see this strain in any coffee shops on my last trip to amsterdam. best bud iv smoked in a while.

The Rom dropped a bomb on my head. Not the smartest idea to take my portable vaporizer loaded up with this particular strain to a bowling alley. Needless to say, I quickly lost interest in the repetitiveness of throwing a heavy ball down a strip of greased flooring. It was one of those midnight bowling situations where they turn the lights down...I simply felt the need to just put on my sunglasses anyway and observe this strange event of black lights, neon colors, and top 40 pop hits from a seated position for the rest of the night.
Really nice, pleasant, competent, clear-headed high. A great daily strain, not a superfun blowout, but more calm, lightly energetic. Rather talky.

Took about 3 good hits from the pipe to get me up to an [8] or so.  Very intense body high but some sort of strange waves of what I imagine uplifted would be like.  Super tired right now which is why I smoked it, so I could sleep better tonight.  Don't really have the munchies which is kind of surprising.  Had a lot of popcorn at the movies so maybe I am just super full.  Getting pretty hard to feel my hands on the keyboard right now.  Harder to concentrate but can force my self into short waves of focussed but that only lasts for about 3 seconds, which is why it has taken me 30 minutes to write that last sentence.  Not a happy or euphoric feeling per say, just neutral, but definitely good for stress relief.  Hope this is long enough, I want that g-d wordsmith badge!

My life's been a circus lately, so when I saw Cotton Candy Kush on my most trusted collective's menu, I figured, why not.  I have seen examples of this strain in pix on the webz, showing vibrant lavender, even pink and blue veins of color running through sugar coated chunks.  My personal sample is sticky icky and bright green with large healthy nugs. It has the occasional streak of purp, but in no way does the lack of wacky colors hurt my opinion of this fine strain.  I have read that it tastes like cotton candy upon exhale, and that the smoke around you can carry heavy hints of the same.  I was skeptical...but like a bearded lady swallowing a sword while riding a unicycle on a tightrope over a sharktank, this shit blew my mind.  And it DOES bring that very sweet sweet 5star kush flavor, but even more than that, it IS a cotton candy-ish blend.  The rush is immediate, with a perfect pressure to the backs of the eyes, a general body relaxation, and of course, as you would expect from this strain, some ridiculous cotton mouth that will choke you out like a midget dressed as a hobo holding one of those little tiny umbrellas and....ok one metaphor too far?  Cotton Candy Kush - get some clowns!

Strong, long lasting energetic fuel. Great for boosting your appetite.
Very strong body effect, mind still focus.
Say goodnight with Kryptonite.

A nice warmth going up my spine.  No extreme emotional effects, just feel normal, not happy or giggly at all.  Smoking it from the pipe tonight and it is super harsh, not sure what is the deal but it burns the back of my throat.  Just a little left of this weed, not sure if I would refill or not when given the opportunity.  Wife just made some nachos and I got distracted.  Came back and was kind of stoked to be coding right now, we'll see how it looks in the morning.
Vaped a bit tonight and feeling pretty good.  Definitely have a supreme case of the munchies, gotta find something healthy to eat.... ya right!

I've had a few samples of J1 now, from a few different collectives, and I gotta say, its just a really nice, well-balanced strain.  Known for its spicy characteristics, a well-grown JackHerer bud will carry a flavor all its own.  A perfect bud for a nice two to three bowl sesh when you aren't quite ready to "clock out" mentally for the day just yet.  Certainly not the type of weed to knock your socks off, just a sweet spicy mellow ride, like surfing at Christmastime

Though not a fan of hybrids in general, I do scoop up some Blue Dream from time to time, usually in the form of a pre-roll - when I just need to get giggly.  Bright green, almost florescent, always fruity always saturated in sugary crystals...red-bearded blueberry bastard I tell ya.. Not sure what it is about this strain, but it leaves me laughing at the stupidest shit all night long, then ZONK out like a light.

Bought some Soul Shine from One Love Beach Club in Long Beach, and boy does the name reflect the bud. Although it's a hybrid, Soul Shine had very powerful sativa effects, and honestly has been one of the most uplifting buds I've ever had the pleasure of smoking. Absolutely no couch lock from this one. Rather, it's extremely energetic, light, airy, and makes you want to do something creative/take a walk/have a stimulating conversation. I highly recommend it.
Ah, Purple Kush. The king of couchlocks. Every time I smoke this I literally want to melt into my bed and remain immobile for a few hours. Gotta love those wicked indicas.
Green crack is a personal favorite of my boyfriend and I. It's always a clean, reliable high that's well-suited for hanging out and home and relaxing, but not being completely out of commission.

Snowcap has become part of my regular rotation, as my sativa of choice.  I still pop for others from time to time, but I try to always have some Snowcap in my cabin!  A great blend of all the qualities you look for in a good smoke.  My next mission is to find some from some different sources for comparison.

I typically gravitate towards couch-lock Indicas, but Strawberry Cough is the exception to the rule. 

The buds tend to be small and dense. The taste is silky smooth, with a distinct berry flavor on exhale. The flavor is intense when smoking, but vaporizing enhances it even more. 

Within 5 minutes I feel the weight of the world removed from my shoulders and become easily amused. After this initial effect I feel drawn to writing music.

Grab some if you can find it.

My wife and I are swingers and we both want to let the Weedmaps World know that it is a fabulous social strain.  Usually if we smoke OG Kush and then have the gimp sh!t on our chests we have trouble feeling the poo and its gooey warmth.  But with the Super Skunk it's like a large Indian that just ate hot curry teamed up with a Mexican and let us have it like Mount St. Hellens just blew its shit-filled top.

Highly recommended for those looking for a nice, cerebral high.  And those who want to FEEL the shit on their chests!
Enjoyed this round very much.  Had a pretty shitty day but this made me feel uplifted and very optimistic.  Had the munchies which is pretty normal, not really any drymouth.

Got a bit of this weed for my birthday, and i have to say i was really impressed with this strain.

You feel happy, willing to do something, not smashed but really stoned.
You can still work and is a really nice for idea's growing.
High THC Level, strong and fruity taste.

Actually one of the best weed i've ever tried.
Strongly recommended.

I've been hanging onto this GFR now for a few weeks, just cant seem to bring myself to choose it over the other strains I've had on hand.  I did grind some down and vape it the other night, which was light years better than piping this foul smelling flower.  I gotta admit, it does the trick, its a dumdum high for a good chunk of time.

Came across a new batch of the Mendo Purps, from a new collective I had never visited, so I had to scoop some up.  I've previously hd this strain from two other sources, and have enjoyed and appreciated it quite a bit each time.  But this latest batch takes the cake.  Large, golf ball sized nugs, deeeeeeeeeeeep purple lots of orange, and just tip to twig in diamondlike trich.  Fruity as hell, I just love this stuff.

This is my favorite to date! Me and my buddy gave it a demo (a well packed bowl) and hot boxed in my car and it brought me to a new level of high that I had never reached! One bowl! I've since had many more fantastic adventures with said weed!
I think I overdid it a bit this time, so incredibly tired and lazy, very hard to come to leafly to actually write this review.

This stuff hit me pretty hard, strong indica, great for sitting here and listening to music.  Fair amount of drymouth but maybe that's because I'm eating chips also.  Definitely not good if you have things to get done, like me, oops.
Second session of the day and the Gc is still giving me some nice lift. Absolutley loving this...

Investigative reports are leading to believe that Bob Marley is fond of this shit. One hundred and twenty min. later I felt like the fist time I heard Zeppelin. Cheeks are red from bursting blood vessels, and I'm on to the next round. Easy smoking' smooth transition into free space. Any music sounds great.
Love Denver Relief's Blue Dream....wOw!

This is an extremely potent strain with a intense powerful high. The high was similar to the high from durban poison, except it lasted a hell of a lot longer. It was a very enjoyable high. Got rushes of energy and these wierd phycadelic-like experiences which were coming and going as i was smoking the blunt. I wouldnt say i was tripping, as that is impossible from consuming marijaunna, but it was just odd. great and extremely enjoyable, but odd. the only downside to this bud is the high didnt last that long, and wore off after about an hour or so. On the positive side there was no burnout, and the bud had a nice fruity lemony taste to it. I would definately recommend this bud. the high it provided me with was very unique and pleasant. This is not for new smokers. This bud also made me very active but, due to the short duration of the high, could be smoked before bed.
THE BEST WEED EVER!
Very mellow, makes me horny most of the time also, Very very fun
Very strong high, wanted to run and jump around and just be goofy
I smoked it with my friends before we went clubbing and we had the time of our lives!

Reading some old reddit classics and really laughing, giggly is good.  Feeling pretty happy, not too tired, having fun searching the interwebs and listening to some fly beats.  Pretty awesome time actually,A++ fast shipping, would buy again.  Trying to read more but keep getting distracted by the itunes visualization on the other screen.
A nice taste, very heavy head high makes your brain feel very blank and at ease.

Really got my mind racing. Weird, yet enjoyable high. Jack Herrer x Shiva Skunk. Could feel the jack herrer genetics in the high, which is great since jack herrer is one of my favorite strains. This bud is good for wake and bakes, and is a good substitute for coffee. There is no burnout from this bud, and i was in a good mood even after my high wore off. The nugs are very sticky and hard to break up and roll with since they get all over and stick to everything. The bud has a really nice taste to it though, and smokes nicely through a not to tightly rolled blunt. When rolling a blunt of this stuff though leave yourself plenty of time. took me almost fifteen minutes to roll when it ordinarily takes me 2-3. most of this time was spent breaking up the weed.  grinder wasnt working that well so i had to break out the scissors. 
nice smoke. potent high that leaves you active and awake.

Can't wait to get my hands on more of this stuff. It's lineage is composed of one of my favourites, grapefruit..the unmistakable smell, the pungent taste..it's a dream. Gets you this strange floaty kind of high while keeping you grounded and maybe even a bit bed/couch locked. I'll have a more accurate description asap, probably within the next three days, I'll put it through my vape for the full experience.

Again, I can't wait to have more of this stuff in my jars. Had a limited quantity this time around, but just enough to get a decent feel for it. Super uplifting, but not purely a daytime smoke! I was able to pass out quickly after getting blasted off of this stuff with my girl. The smell and taste are simply overwhelming. Super euphoric, super fantastic. Expect a better review in the next two-three days.
One hit wonder.  Can be a little too anxious, but never bad.

Too much anxiety?  I had to take an ativan.  Could also be the dx.  Drowsy and very red eyes.
Personal favorite.  Makes me want to take a bike ride or rock out.

Great bud, smell's better then it's name would imply (and that's hard to top) id say better than any bud I've smelt in some time. 

   The look of the bud is very appealing with a rich light green color, frosted white all over, the weed looks wet. SLH sticks to the fingers and scissors with little pressure applied..dankness..Not much to say about the hairs medium orange lightly covering the weed.  

    Usually I like smoking to get sleepy and have that melt in the couch feeling, but sometimes you need to get things done and take a smoke break, so recently looking for a "daytime" high that wont leave me flopped out for the whole day.

   I found this SLH great smooth smoke tastes like it smells maybe more sweet than sour and still true to lemon name. Keeps me high and active I'm diggin it! Great alternative to the K.O. weed and still has a strong buzz. 9/10

Mk Ultra is a heavy hitter K.O. bud. I smoked some this past weekend and got too stoned, went to that achy point where i couldn't get up without being sore puts your body in instant nap mode. The buds are very thick really dense weed, the smell is that of a "purple" with a super minty fresh alpine scent.
  the bud has multi shades of green not very hairy but the hairs are deep orange with a small tint of purple ( i like the color) semi frosted nothing impressive. tastes good very smooth taste stays in your mouth for a bit its nice.
   As I stated earlier this bud is strong you cant casually smoke this all day you will be to stoned to function! smoked in a session its great but leave it at that, not the kinda doja you want to have around all day. 9/10

An incredable nice strain, looks a little brown in the bag but counters that nicely with a strong citrus smell. Once you grind it up the smell almost becomes unbearable. I wouldn't recommend smoking this before you have done your work for the day, Lemon Skunk will sink you into your chair, and you ain't getting outta it again. A very nice weed, would highly recommend it to my friends and hope to have more in coming days.

There were 2 blunts rolled up and there were at least 5 or 6 heads in the room passing it around. We all had good hits from the 2 blunts. But this lasted about a good 15 minutes. Right after I hit the couch and BOOM I turned into a lazy motherfucker. Sitting down on the couch, not wanting to get up. I wanted to nap so bad, and I did for a bit but the noise around me didn't help. Nonetheless I got my rest. My high didn't last long. 15 minutes of being energetic and 30 or less minutes of being a lazy couch potato. Odd first experience, but it was chill.

The nugs were very dense and very dark green.  The budtender told me it was Outdoor Sour D. Feeling pretty happy, trying to think about stressful things but my mind won't let me.  Got a little work done at the beginning but now enjoying just hanging out and listening to music.  Just took a couple hits from a grape ape joint, sleepy time.

A wonderful hybrid consisting of 90% Sativa and 10% Indica; Mexican Sativa crossed with Chemdawg. Definitely more of a daytime strain that's great for any anxiety or stress I might have, also, I really want to go to the beach :)

One of my favorite strains that's not hard to find at any of my cali clinics. I don't see it in New England, but when I got a hold of it over there, it was quite a hit. Good when you don't want the munchies and need a little boost of the sillies and some energy. I've always been able to be sociable even in the most overwhelming situations and usually get my motivation on.   People tend to be surprised by how much the 'crack' part of the name really describes the high.

Sour Diesel is one of my all-time-favorites. The smell is deliciously Sativa and very penetrating, this isn't the bottle you want to open up in a room you don't want smelling like scrumptious weed. Sour D can be described as being one of the most euphoric and uplifting strains of cannabis with the power to bring out one's creative self. Music is extremely enjoyable and as well as great conversation or philosophizing :)

I love the coloring of this strain. It's so dark purple that it's almost black with little bits of green peaking through here and there. Covered with crystals to the point of having to scrape them off my fingers. There isn't a lot of leaf but the leaves themselves are worthy of remaining untrimmed. The pods themselves are full and dense supporting a good amount of hair too.

Very smooth hitting with pleasant mild flavor. The smell is very strong and distinct but not typical with a hint of something that almost smells of nutmeg. The high comes on pretty powerfully but in a smooth controlled way. Hard to describe. Feels like it's about to knock you over but never quite does and some how you know it.

Excellent quality plant. The nugs were absolutely covered in crystals to the point where it was hard to tell what colors were in the plant. Upon closer inspection you can see a dense structure with rich purple and green colors hiding under the trichomes. The strain is very very dense.

The smoke is very tasty but also thick which makes for a slightly less smooth smoke. It's not harsh from the herb but from the fact that it smokes so well with so much THC. The high sets on fast and strong with a good kick to the head followed my a warm systemic dissemination of the high throughout the rest of the body. This strain is great for a daily smoking strain because of it's strength in my book.

Took that long and strange trip to my not so local baker and scored more of this Organic Diesel, I'm unclear as to why it's called that..as all of the herb I smoke is grown organically..hm. But I did do some research and I've concluded that it's kosher to call it 'Organic' Diesel. It's not like Sour Diesel, I'm guessing from research that it's a cross of Diesel 77 and Diesel 48. It tastes good, a nice mellow diesel taste that doesn't linger long but if you get a taste of it, it's a super potent one. While the initial high isn't lengthy..the buzz lasts for up to two hours. This is also the first Sativa dominate hybrid I've had in ages that leaves me satisfied even when trying to sleep, a great all around high that I'm glad to be getting to know over the next week of my smoking ;D

The stone of the Slh can take a nice hold, but it's not at all unmanageable. It's simply the combination of the taste, the smell and the high that makes this quite a memorable strain. So distinct and so clean, it makes you really appreciate cannabis and what a wonderful plant it truly is.
Such a nice strain...and good friend.

This stuff is dark, and smelly..it also has an interesting/odd taste to it, leaving me to think that someone may have cut a corner while making this hash. It's very dense for bubble hash and doesn't crumble when you try to mold it, must be pretty fresh then! Anyway, it's good stuff through and through..I might wanna get a gram of this stuff for myself! ;D

Pleasant high. a creeper. i smoked a couple hours ago and i am still very, very high . it takes about 30-35 minutes to fully kick in, and about 4 hours before the high gradually starts to fade off.  the buds are wider at the top similar to jack herrer, except they are not quite as big and more resinous. it looks like it was dipped in resin. the bud is covered in dark orange hairs that are well trimmed. the stem has a slightly more sour taste to it then most buds, and it has a citrus/ diesel smell to it. this is a very potent, sativa dominant, high which provided me with some energy. this bud is good for the movies and good to get outside because it is very visually enhancive. i enjoyed/ am enjoying this bud very much.

this is a good looking bud with a high that hit me right away. the high was sativa dominant, and i felt some energy at first, but this faded and there was a strong burnout afterwords. i think this strain is over rated. it was alright and looks and smells fine, but it just wasnt a very impressive high at all. some buds just make you feel happy and great and this wasnt one of them. just your average bud. nothing special. looks are a little deceptive.

For those of you with Anxiety or Stress: I used to like smoking, but I hated it at the same time cause of the anxiety I would get so I put it off for a while and was even against smoking. Now that I understand different strains and have become more educated and have tried this, I must say this is my absolute favorite.. I tend not to stray too far from Blue Dream... I can smoke this in comfort... my stress and anxiety levels plummet, my thoughts are super clear, I'm happy and very worry free on this. All your stresses will leave your mind and your body... this is my baby. The strength of this isn't what makes it rate so high. It's how relaxing it is that makes it superior in my book. This is one to enjoy and hang out with some friends or just listen to some music by yourself. Definitely a recommendation for those with anxiety/stress disorders.

One of my personal top strains. The pungent lemon/diesel/pine scent is a defining characteristic of this beautiful lemon thai/chemdawg/Hindu (sometimes Afghany) Kush cross. Lasts a while even in those with a high "tolerance"; For me this flower produces a soaring cerebral effect, followed by a rapid decline in energy and usually a nap. Great for any time after noon, particularly about an hour and a half before bedtime.
Good work time strain. Perfect for medicating at times when a hard burnout cannot be afforded. Produces a strong, clear head high without weighing me down.

Medicated with some blue dream whilst awaiting a public transport vessel; very strong, i repeat very strong head high. This sweet smelling flower definitely lives up to its name as it produced a stony, dreamlike sensation which I enjoyed riding onto the bus and all the way home.

Not the highest quality AK-47 around, but definitely not to be underestimated. The distinct AK (sandalwood-ish) smell is quite apparent, this is a unique scent among cannabis and intrigues me. Long flowers, not the densest but definitely not plain-water outdoor; I can tell that this medication was grown with love! I medicated with this strain almost exclusively over the course of a week and have to say that the most defining characteristic of this flower is the smell and taste; a close second is the nice hybrid effect complements of a light body high combined with a mild and even, clear head high. Again, not the most potent, high-quality AK-47 (as i know exists out there) but definitely a nice all day flower for guaranteed enjoyment.
A very distinct strong piney smell. Piney, Earthy taste. Pretty smooth smoking, not too harsh. A very uplifting clear high.

Good smoke. Has a lot of medicinal qualities, it's a hard smoke, but if your a fan of a good indica this strains for you. glistens in the lights, wouldnt put it past me if the THC count is higher then 30%.
some nice sativa, good smoke when your about to go do something. tasted good a lot of flavor. medicinal quality for sure but i've had kinder sativa from dispensaries. again a good smoke
Winner of the Cannabis Cup '09 Indica. Very medicinal strain. Instant head that radiates warmth through the chest area. Very relaxing and not too sleepy. Almost all of the seeds gave great phenos!

it's a really tasty Og but i have yet to find a good batch, most batch's that i've tried are not properly flushed (don't know why) and are lacking strength but still pretty strong kind of a given for any Og.

This bud is a creeper, and it is very, very potent. do not drive or operate heavy machinary after smoking. it takes about 45 minutes for the buzz to fully kick in, with a body stone that doesnt put you to sleep, and last a little over four hours. i actually got a slight amount of energy from this bud for the first few hours. unfortunatly the come down from this bud will knock you on your ass, which is why i didnt give it a higher rating. besides the harsh comedown this bud is a very pleasant smoke. it has a sweet citrus taste and a citrus/ diesel smell. the high put a smile on my face like white widow or good jack herrer. it was an extremely fun and enjoyable high. this bud made everything better and more fun to do. my appitite increased significantly and i ended up eating a whole apple pie by accident in addition to plenty of other food. i also found it difficult to stand when smoking this bud which was weird. it was overwhelming when i was smoking it towards the end of the blunt and i though i was gonna have a heart attack. i also felt like i weighed next to nothing. once i was able to raid the kitchen though i completely forgot my heart felt like it was about to jump out of my chest, even though i was still getting higher at the time. this bud is great for enhancing everything. it made everything a lot more fun. i would not recommend smoking it if you plan on accomplishing anything though.

As a cancer patient, I have been through dozens of strains and use my weed to keep me out of the hospital. I could dose about every 90 minutes to replace 10 mg of oxycontin every four hours and a continuous Fentanyl patch. If you know your opiates, then you know this is serious medicine.

I lost nearly half of my body weight and GDK helped me turn the corner to avoid going on a feeding tube.

While I can get relief with many other strains for most situations, GDK helps in EVERY situation and sometimes is the only strain in my arsenal that gets the job done.

Smoke Report

Intrto- LVPK is the best overall strain I have smoked to date, for one major reason. I am a daily smoker and one of the most important qualities for a strain to have is potency over time and quantity. I gain a high tolerance to the majority of strains I smoke after about a quarter ounce, so any strain I can smoke an ounce of and it still gets me baked really stands out. I have smoked lvpk now for the last 6 months or so, and it still gets me baked as a cake. 

Smell- This strain smells like Afghan Hash, Floral Purfume, and a slight skunkyness.

Taste- Taste Floral, Fruity, and Hashy

Look- It has dense nugs that turn lavender on the tops and tips. The nug sturcture is indica but crowns out. The Frost can cover all the way out to the medium fan leaves. It gets just as frosty Tom Hill's as Deep Chunk. The bud grows golfball to baseball size tops. the BEST part though is the nugs from the bottom of the plant are dense as the ones on the tops which is also very rare.

High- The high is very strong, and it is a hybrid feeling high. At first this strain is so strong that most people wont move for about 2 hours, but not because of couch lock. The strain can actually get overwhelming in visual and body effects for even experienced smokers. Once I got a little used to it, I started to move around more. I always end up listening to about 2 hours of music everytime I smoke it. The best way to describe the feeling of this strain is "Euphoric Visual Comfort" It makes me feel like the universe is perfect.

Summary. This strain is the only strain I would ever give a 10.

A staunch 50/50 sativa/indica hybrid, Broke Diesel is by far the most hallucinogenic weed I've ever smoked, and I'd say one of the most potent ever. A bong sesh gave me major body rushes and mind-warps, and also leant a discernible ecstasy-induced nature to my perception. As far as scent and taste go, the best way I can think of to describe Broke Diesel is to compare it to the wafting aroma of diesel rising from the fuel tank of my tractor, superimposed upon the dewy scent of morning tumble weeds and creosote. This strain definitely falls amongst my top three favorite tokes of all time. And the best part of it all? I picked it up for just $260 an ounce.

This strain is a favorite among many because it provides a pleasing body stone combined with an energized head buzz. It is quite well balanced and relaxing in every sense of the term. I'd love to give this strain a higher overall rating, but the buzz length held it back a bit. Had this at Stone's Cafe in Amsterdam, and after 2 monster hits off a joint, I was totally plowed. In a good way. At first I didn't think anything was happening, so I took another hit, but then a few minutes later...KABOOM! Shit is creeperific. Great high, was in great spirits, talkative as hell, and just generally feeling fantastic. But, unfortunately, that didn't last nearly as long as I'd like it to last. The effects almost seem to go away at a snap of a finger, but it's a pretty terrific strain if you're looking to get trashed for about an hour, then go out. Not too too munchy either.

Simply one of the best out there. Smooth on the smoke, smooth on the exhale, strong and fast. Absolutely caked in crystals, smelled like dank.. not sure how else to describe it. Came on like a freight train after a few hits, and had me totally stoned, then baked, for over 2 hours. After sitting outdoors at a coffeeshop in Amsterdam and people watching while totally silent for an hour, my buddy and I went to the Van Gogh and stared in awe, laughing like idiots for another hour. On the walk back we absolutely crushed lunch, threw in some beers, and, totally plowed, went back to the hotel to crash. Maybe my best stone of my lifetime, I can't say enough. A nice, pleasant hazy head high, with a body finisher. Absolutely no burn out whatsoever. I woke up from my nap feeling like a million bucks. Highly recommended.

This is to London as NYC Diesel is to NYC.. almost the default pot you can get from the local dealer. I've heard people totally rave about this stuff, and I'm not entirely sure why. I will say this: feeling happy and euphoric while at the same time being lazy and talkative is pretty rare for a pure Indica. I smoked a few of these in joint form outside at a coffeeshop in Amsterdam while drinking beers and talking to other shop-goers and had a great time. Not the pot to smoke if you're looking to get completely baked and stay in, but not a bad Indica if you want to be social. Prepare for a biblical case of the munchies on the come down..

Eh. I had this stuff at the Greenhouse in Amsterdam, and given that fact just assumed it'd be awesome. Boy was I wrong. It was like "marijuana light". Initial euphoria and focus of a Sativa, with a tinge of a body high/heavy eyes of an Indica - which I'd assume is rare in a pure Sativa. Maybe this particular strain wasn't any good, but I found it to be pretty JV. Smells wonderful though, and tastes smooth and light. I was abnormally chatty though, so I guess that's good. Music was also pretty awesome with this stuff, and there was zero paranoia. I prefer Sour Diesel for pure Sativas, but this wouldn't be bad in a pinch, just don't expect to be stoned for more than an hour.

Got this batch from a friend here in NYC. Not the strongest stuff I've ever had, but a crystal clear head high with the tiniest hints of a body stone on the finish. Doesn't last long, even after about 15-20 minutes I feel the onset of the come down phase. This stuff made me want to get up and do something, so I'm guessing it'll be perfect for a wake and bake, or chores or the DMV.. whatever. The stuff I had in Amsterdam was MUCH stronger on the high, so I'd say somewhere in between is ideal. Overall, not so bad for the once in a whiles.. but not so good for the everydayer.

My favorite strain on my trip to Amsterdam. Had this at Baba, and Stone's Cafe. The latter really killed it. Stuff was awesome. People that are unsure of themselves socially, or who may become anxious in public would love this stuff. I was the mayor of Amsterdam for an hour or so, talking to anyone that would listen. I was also in a fantastic mood the whole time... if only people who take paxil, zoloft, etc knew about this stuff. The smell actually does have the tiniest hints of dark chocolate, with an overall dank of high quality stuff. I wish I had this stuff in the States, I'd smoke it everyday. Also pretty munchy on the finish, so prepare for that.

Had this up in Tahoe. My buddy had it for authentic medicinal purposes (he has a pinched nerve in his neck caused by a spine injury). At first, it hits you like a mutherf__king 18 wheeler, but settles in and you feel faaaantastic. Felt great about life, and the surroundings just seem to blur into one mass while I focused on my beer, or the TV, or whatever. Nice and even the whole way too, once the first 15 minutes were over. Smells like a Kush, with nice skunky weed smell in general. Not sure I could do this everyday, but for having some friends over and listening to tunes, this stuff is great. You maintain control with the ability to be social, but could also sit in and order 5 pizzas while watching movies.

This strain of Blueberry Kush was a cross between Blueberry and Purple Kush. It forms very crystal covered buds with purple highlights throughout the leaves. The buds are extremely dense and resemble cheese when dry and broken. The smell is very citrus like, with a very mild smell until it is broken open, which then rushes your nose with lemon/orange like overtones.

Smoking this strain is an experience. Smoking in a glass bowl will have your entire head feeling numb off a couple of good hits. It hits you shortly after you exhale, and then keeps creeping up for a good 15 minutes until you reach the peak of the high. It then soars at that point for at least an hour before slowly trailing off. Once you get to the 2 hour mark it has mostly worn off leaving you relaxed and very mellow. Although it has a very Indica appearance, this hybrid is not going to put you to sleep like most Indica's. You will normally want to get out and do something other than sit around.

This a great bud if you want an expansive mind state yet aren't couchlocked and you are able to effectively communicate your thoughts.

OG Kush is Sativa dominant strain that lifts you up into the clouds. Strong ass head high! Considered one of So Cals ultimate strains, OG Kush is known for its very dense buds, copious resin, and high THC Levels. Clean, some what smooth  pine taste with a slight hint of sour lemon. OG Kush leaves you with a strong sativa head high.

Purple Kush is one purple strain that stands out on its own. Straight solid purple, dense buds with plenty of resin! Super sweet skunk smell. Stong grape taste! Purple Kush is a great strain for medicating. Good for relaxing, pain relief, and loss of sleep. Heavy Indica head and body high.

Hillside Medical; 1/8th for $60.

This was some very good bud. It looked a little leafier than elite OG Kush and the smell wasn't as dank as I would have liked, but it was pretty tasty. It had nice citrus overtones and a delicate lemony taste right underneath, with the smoke thickly aromatic. 

It kept me high for a curiously long two hours; by the 100th minute I still felt a little high. I have a pretty high tolerance, so this was pretty surprising.

I was at Barnes and Noble after smoking this, and I ended up buying two Cannabis magazines and three  books. One was a social science/human behavioral work, another was related to history, and the last was about learning how to read literature critically.

Silver Pearl is a beautiful flower, a sativa dominant hybrid with just enough of an indica kick to sit you down.  My batch came in small to medium sized nugz that literally stuck to the LID of the jar.  Bustling with a microscopic milky way of trich coverage and sprouting more red hairs at odd angles than a ginger on his 14th birthday, the Silver Pearl lives up to its name with its opaque appearance and rarity on most menus.  It smokes just as great as it looks, with a slightly skunky taste and smell, and just a snapper at a time to keep from choking to death.  It hits hard and immediate, leaving you swearing that you just ripped a heavy indica at first, until you realize that you just spent the past hour with a slack jaw trying to figure out how to harness the power of the "sphere" for the good of mankind.  Do not pass up Silver Pearl if it crosses your path.

The buzz itself doesn't last for super long, but it leaves you with a feeling of optimism, happiness, and motivation that lasts for a really long time afterwards (at least three hours AFTER the buzz dies down). It's the most clear-headed high I've ever had, and by far the best motivator strain if I ever need to get anything done. If you want a strain that helps you actually accomplish things this is the way to go.

Really floaty and euphoric. I feel really happy, dont feel any pain. The first half hour I could definitely feel the indicia side of this hybrid. Total couch lock. After that I felt more up and energetic, like I was ready to clean or do homework just ready to get stuff done. But I also felt like chilling and watching tv. So Id say its pretty balanced, you could do anything.

I was fortunate enough to get some organic outdoor LA Confidential from Humboldt County this fall at harvest time. This strain is truly top of the line, and there's a reason that it's one of the most popular medical strains in California. 

The flavor of the buds is unmatched - I agree with the other reviewer who said it tastes like wintergreen upon inhalation. When you exhale, it tastes a bit fruity/lemony, and you get a distinctly skunky taste. The smell of the smoke is fantastic and classic.

I do not recommend this bud for anxiety or sleep, as it has a lot of euphoric, head buzz qualities to it, unlike some other indicas that may be better for such medical applications. After I smoked my first hit of it, I had a grin plastered across my face. I think this strain has good pain relief qualities, but I have smoked other strains before bed to calm down because this bud makes me high, happy, and jubilant. I already made sure to secure the rest of the batch. :)
