This is my favorite strain of all time.  A real good indica with some lovely effects.  It starts by making your body tingle and buzz.  That buzz gives way to this real nice wave of euphoria and a pleasant kind of vertigo.  It's not that you can't tell what's up and what's down, it's that you are so relaxed that you don't care.  For a while you get lost in your couch (or bed) trying to guess what's up and what's down.  The giggles come on in the downward tail.  Never releases hard.  Doesn't leave you feeling dirty...clean finishing.  This is a must try for anyone looking for a pleasant and relaxing strain and an absolute MUST TRY for anyone new to medical marijuana.

It all depends on the breeder and grower and if they got real deal or if they got fake n make clones or if the lineage it true or tinkered with. that's what makes marijuana wonderful it's very flexible. here's a new review i just did for a cut of skywalker.

Strain: OG Skywalker
Genetics: Indica Dominant hybrid
Lineage: (Mazar x blueberry) x O.G.

Under a pure white light this skywalker appears light orange, light green, yellow, amber and white. The orange hair's have a pink hue to them and look like they were cross stitched into the swollen calyx's and bubbling or billowing type bud structure.

The smell is quiet unique as well. It's minty, smokey, earthy, skunky and sweet with a tad bit of sour fume.

The bud looks and Feels dense but it easily breaks away and turns to soft sticky goodness like an OG cut would! This definitely leans way on the OG side of the mix. In fact if i were to take a shot in the dark based on structural appearance, the fumes/sour overtones and the extreme heavy sativa effect i would say this plant has some headband or sour d in it's lineage; Most likely introduced from the OG side....

Once again this has been dried and cured properly as I've come to expect with ICOC over the last 4 or 5 years. Proper drying and curing is crucial for a good looking, proper tasting, extra smooth, perfectly potent and extremely aromatic medical grade marijuana.

The high feels a little more on the sativa side than indica. My built in meter is telling me 60% sativa by the feel of things. To me that's a perfect ratio anyway, it's balanced. You get the focused, cerebral and sometimes psychedelic stoned effect from the sativa and just as much lethargic, couch locked, pain numbing body high and sleep inducing effect from the Indica.

The high lasts about 45 minute's and really induced a heavy appetite during that time.

I highly recommend this from one patient to another seeking well grown, top shelf A+ meds.

Thanks for reading,
-Kushits

After a while I began to feel a weird kind of tension on the upper portion of my trapezius muscles. I confess this happens with many other strains of weed but I was hoping Trainwreck would not do that do me.

A doctor friend was suffering from fluish stomach cramps. I suggested maybe a teeny toke of white rhino to ease his suffering. 

He declined at first - he wasn't sure, but assumed that pot weakens your immune system like alcohol. I made a case (in layman's logic) for why I assumed it would be the reverse - low toxic intake, immediate overall relaxation -  and convinced him. He smoked a cautious bowl. 

And was glad he did. He agreed that the acheyness, general discomfort and irritability of mild fluishness all evaporated leaving him feeling ready to rest and his body to mend.

I'm rating this strain a 10 because it is perfect for me. I've grown it from seed, and have also purchased it many times from dispensaries, all with virtually the same effect. Bright neon green with lots of orange pistils, and totally caked with sugary trichomes. Definately sativa dominant, but not speedy and racy. Very uplifting and positive high. Can always lift me out of any bad mood and put a smile on my face. I also have chronic anxiety and Jillybean completely puts me at ease. Great daytime smoke. Good for being outside, taking a cruise into the country, and just relaxing and listening to some good tunes. I can also smoke this in the evening and have no trouble falling asleep. True Blueberry x OG Kush is a very unique strain in that it has more CBD than THC. Research in FOR-REAL, PEER-REVIEWED medical journals suggests that CBD is an effective anti-inflammatory and analgesic, and may help with Alzheimer's as well as the onset of blindness in diabetics. But, you know, that's all experimental. 

For me, personally.. I honestly don't really even get "high" with this stuff, which I assume is due to the low THC content. It feels like Valium but without the edge/side effects or harsh come-down. The only buzz is in the body, and that buzz is significantly lighter than in most indicas (it feels more like an indica despite being sativa-dominant). I've felt sedation and a small amount of couchlock. Now, to the real stuff: it is by far the most effective painkiller of any strain I have tried, and I love that about it. I'm not a huge fan of strains that give you a weird mix of effects -- I like when strains are really good at one particular thing, whether that's getting me up, putting me to sleep, making a bad movie better, or in this case, taking the pain away after a long day. 

One more thing -- because it's CBD-heavy, I would imagine most people trying it are probably after its potent medical benefits, and a large subset of those people may use vaporizers. Every cannabinoid has a different vaporizing temperature. CBD needs more heat -- specifically 206.3 (404.3F) degrees in order to vaporize. So make sure your vaporizer is properly adjusted and can reach that temperature -- otherwise, you'll need to smoke it.

As it turned out, we were so lazy we didn't have the will to get up to snack or change the DVD.  So, we just watched the same episode of the Blue Planet 3 times.  Loved it!

   [CON:] Not a good weed for having sex with...you'll have no motivation.  Body exploring, maybe, but not sex. :-(

The strongest strain i've ever encountered. Had a bad reaction last night after having smoked it several times before. The only difference i can think of is that I had caffeine earlier in the day, and later in the night, which i never do. I can only think that having taken a large hit right before laying down to bed had something to do with this strange reaction. My muscles were tight, especially in my neck. My legs and upper body experienced large spasms, my mind was racing, and I had to meditate for an hour just to get the thoughts out of my head. I was insanely thirsty, and the back of my head ached. I had almost 7 glass of water, and instantly I had cotton mouth. I was freezing, I had 5 blankets on and was still not warm. I had to consult with my hubby to help calm me down. I felt euphoric, and at moments, in control, but would easily loose this control second by second. I was able to see outside myself and from others perspectives. Anything that i felt was an emotion, was from someone else's perspective. I personally had to confront over 50 situations in my mind that I had to answer to and resolve or they would loop endlessly in my head. I often had to get up and get more water, or focus on something else. I watch a movie which helped for longer periods of time, but the anxiety of the experience was difficult to put into check. I had thoughts that I was loosing control, and moments of paranoia where I felt I might have had a heart attack or a brain hemorrhage.  It only subsided 4 or 5 hours later, when I was finally warm, and my thoughts were sorted. I am tempted to explain this reaction to my dispensary, in case there is something with the strain itself. Perhaps it's not a pure form of the plant and there is another strain mixed in? Perhaps went I inhaled from the pipe, the bitter and thickness of the smoke was an indication? I seriously knew something was different with this. I'm not the only one who has had a similar reaction, just two weeks ago almost the same physical reaction was experienced by a friend with the same strain and batch where we got it.  I must call them to let them know. I will not try this again unless I can verify that the contents are pure.

I got this by the recommendation from Cindy (the sales clerk at my cannabis club).  I was dealing with some chronic pain and was looking for something to help...
   Well, within about 20 minutes of vaping this stuff my pain totally went away.  I had been suffering all day long and had taken every kind of over the counter pain meds available - Nuthin'!  A few hits of this and I felt great.  A couple of weeks later my grown-up adult daughter was suffering from a painful kink in her neck and shoulders all day long.  Again, non of the pain killers did anything except irritate her stomach.  After a few hits of this, she was pain free and raiding the kitchen.
    [PROS:] Great for muscle related pain relief.  Being mellow, relaxed and chillin'.  Allows you to sleep very well. And, lets you stay in a pretty good/happy mood.
    [CONS:] Not good for operating large machinery or sharp implements (don't ask).  
    [SUMMERY:]  This is a typical indica that will slow you down and relax you.  It is easy to get a heavy buzz, but you will still have a pretty clear head for normal function and mobility.  There is a bit of the happy bug in this bud.  So, even if you are totally mellowed out and just zoning out to Dr. Who, you will still be feeling in a good, fun, happy mood and will giggle at the little things (like Burger King commercials - again, don't ask).

I tried J1 on a whim, before I found this site and truly educated myself. I'm a female who suffers from PMS related depression/anxiety. One hit of J1 and my irritation, depression, and anxiousness melts away. It starts a little sleepy for me. Calm. Then ten mins later euphoria. Happy. Overwhelming happy. I want to hug everyone. I get chatty, giddy, and giggly. That effect stays with me for about an hour. Smoke too much and I get a little spaced out, but happily so. Not good for sleeping, as it makes me bouncy and energetic once the euphoria kicks in. The comedown is easy, like being gently set back to earth from a fluffy cloud. No sleepy comedown, no hangover. I am now anxious to try true Jack Herer, which J1 was created from. I would purchase J1 again in a heartbeat.

I've had a few ounces of this over the last year, so I am quite familiar. PK has a high THC content (15-28%) and is a cross between Purple Afghani and Hindu Kush. The most recent strain I got was very high quality and upon smoking a tiny amount (to sample for the first time) I almost felt a happy, uplifting, euphoric type high (on a small scale) similar to a sativa.

 Don't get me wrong though this is strong Indica, it can be sedating, lead to couchlock and the munchies. I found my limbs would feel very tingly along with the back on my neck and it felt at times like my whole body was getting a massage, so this good to pain and muscle aches. 

Overall it's great medicine, very chilled, I would recommend using it later in the evening as if you have to do something, you won't want to leave you place if you get too baked. The high tends to be a happy high with sativa-esc (trippy) overtones. Being primarily an indica you don't get a strong energetic feeling from it, but certainly has uplifting characteristics.

This one is a creeper too. Taking a hit you might have to wait 30 seconds to a few minutes to feel the full effects.

Overall well worth it, certainly a top 10 strain.

OUR NEW FAVORITE!!!



   A Sativa/Indica hybrid leaning mostly toward the Sativa.  It's a rather sweet, floral smelling bud.  With a vaporizer (325F), the taste is mild - nearly non-existent.  The buds are quite small - finger tip sized or smaller - but packs a BIG punch!



   Previous to trying this strain for the first time, my wife and I had a deep & emotional, personal problems discussion - Major downer.  We were also quite tired and it was 11pm.  We wanted a little up beat on the evening...



   It hit her almost immediately and hit me faster than most others.  We went from bummed to happy and energetic in no time.  ALL of our previous issues were completely forgotten.  We had never watched Glory Days before...It was great! So were the commercials.  After that we were hooked on Cheaters until 2am.  I have never seen my wife laugh so hard for so long - she was 100% pure happiness.



   [PROS:] Highly uplifting, energetic, euphoric, and fun.  A clear headed high.  Great for watching funny movies, TV or just commercials.  Would also be good for small groups, party games, video games and/or sex (I'm talking about sex for two, but if the whole group wants in...Well, it should be good for that, too).  Munchie cravings are low, too.  Oh, be prepared to get talkative...



   [CONS:] This is NOT a stone out, zone out, watch Baraka kinda herb. Don't use it if you want to get some sleep or down an x-large pizza by yourself.  And, be prepared to listen to everyone being chatty...



   [SUMMERY:]  This is what I call "getting high".  You'll still have lots of functionality and comprehension while you enjoy the fact that absolutely nothing in this world is bad, sad or ugly.  You'll be energized, awake and aware.  Expect lots of fun and laughter.  This is one to be shared with others.  Don't be surprised if Blue Dream has become your new favorite, too...

Blueberry from Dutch passion is a great smoke.  They combined the Dj short Blueberry with a higher yielding strain to create a great high yield, high resin and flavor hybrid.  When grown right with careful attention to organic feeding and PH the outcome is colas with blue, red, purple and green.  The taste is blueberry with hints of citrus that the afgani male added, but you can still relate it to the original Oregon blueberry.  Very narcotic if harvested late, but the best high when it is harvested early for a soaring cerebral high and a fresh taste.  Can be very good pain meds but needs to be harvested at the right time to get a narcotic medicinal high.

Champagne is a cross between a Pure himalayan sativa and an afgani X hash plant.  The Pheno is various from pure indica to pure sativa.  The main dominate gene in the Champagne a soaring cerebral high that is good for meditation and relaxing.  The high doesn't have much narcotic punch to it, but always packs a head rush that last for several minutes then gently letting you ease into a meditative relaxed state.  This strain was made popular by the King of Nepal, one of the early advocates of making fine hash in the U.S.  This strain makes some of the best hash you could find.  With none of the woody, spicy, or astringent notes that are found in some afgani hashes.  The hash from the Champagne is of the highest order.  Fruity and fresh with some spice notes reminiscent of Nepalese temple balls of lore.  An excellent strain for psychological disorders and deep meditation.

Could be possibly used as an anti-emetic, but the anxiety that comes with the high may be counter productive.  This stain is person specific and does not appeal to most medical smokers.  Created for high yield and not much else.

This high is best for an attitude change without any sedative qualities.  Purely head high with no body except when grown outdoors.  Outdoor gigabud is as narcotic as opium. I liked this strain very much. At the time when I was smoking it, I had quite a bit of nausea and Grape Ape made this unpleasantness vanish. It also helped to relax both the body and mind. The original UK cheese that surfaced in the 90s was a skunk # 1 from sensi seeds that was grown and cloned over several years during in which the potency and flavor seemed to intensify which is not uncommon in nearly pure sativa's.  I have observed this in original chocolate thai where the potency and vigor increased over a number of years reaching a peak at year 3 or 4.   Skunk#1 is Columbian Gold x Acapulco Gold/Afgani.  The high can be very sedative like an indica if harvested in the late amber headed trichome stage.  However the more soaring cerebral effects go wasted in the late stage and are better appreciated in the clear/milky stage with no amber tichs.  As well as a more soaring high the taste is much more fresh.  An extremely uplifting giggly happy smoke with a nice mellow body.  The great thing about this particular skunk is that you don't build a tolerance quickly and there is no ceiling on the high even if you did.  Not your bland indoor grown indica here.  There is a certain old school flavor to the cheese that is somewhat hashy,earth with newer fruit flavors and an undeniable stench of tangy blue and parmesan cheeses.  Great for several medical conditions, mine being for emetic needs, it meets the needs of a wide variety of palates:)

Bubba Kush an excellent indica.  The Kush genetics really shine thru with this strain.  A nice pine smell with hints of citrus and wood.  A very expansive smoke, but pleasant.  There are different phenotypes of the bubba kush.  I've had the west coast version and it is leaning more on the kush side of it's genes favoring high resin and round compact nugs.  Greenhouse seeds has a bubble gum tasting pheno that blends the two parent strains nicely.  A good choice for any smoker:)

I'd purchased this to try, without knowing it's powers.  I read from this site how strong a medicine this is, especially when it comes to insomnia.  At the time I bought this stuff, I didn't realize that I was coming down with a terrible flu with body aches, diarrhea, and the stomach cramps that are associated with that.  I decided to take some of this just before bedtime and soon I was asleep... for two hours.  I woke up in pain and eventually, I decided to take some more and was amazed to have the cramps lessen and lessen, and me then falling asleep again.  Very nice.

The high is soaring and mellow with a more sativa high at first in small amounts then sedative and narcotic at higher consumption rates.  A decent medicinal strain.  Good for making extracts:)

U.K. Cheese is a perfect example of a hybrid cannabis plant. This indica dominant crossbreed is widely grown in the UK, hence the name. Dense lite, green nuggets. I noticed the similar cheese type aroma after eating some Ben&Jerry's cheesecake brownie ice cream. The taste and smoke are strong but not to pungent, with spicy skunk-like undertones. The Cheese high creates a feeling of great euphoria which comes on nice and smooth. The high opens the mind while relaxing the body and will last a long time. Very strong clear, yet stoney high.

DJ short's Blueberry is one of the finest berry strains out there.  Under optimum conditions Blueberry actually has hues of blue and smells like blueberry muffins. Colors and light seem very enhanced.  The buds are dense and round and covered with trichomes. Sour D is a great strain that isn't appreciated enough.  There are many variations of the D, but none come close to the potency or the high of this particular Diesel phenotype.  Very much sativa in it's growth habits but displaying a wider leaf morphology.  A hard one to grow for beginners, but it pays off in yield and potency after 8-10 weeks of flowering.  The effect of Sour D is purely medicinal in many forms.  It has an excellent anti-depression effect as well as a narcotic pain relief.  All without the lazy effects of some of the more powerful narcotic indicas.  The D will take you higher almost instantly upon the exhale and can sometimes be too much for those not familiar with it's head rush high.  Like the rocket ship of weed, the D will put you in outerspace.

If you are an insomnia sufferer, SSS's Lavender is the strain you are looking for. The nugs are well-cured, on the dense side, with a light purple hue all over. It has a nice citrus scent with flowery overtones, lending it a sweet lavender scent. 

But you aren't reading this for what the cannabis looked like, are you?

The heads over at SSS should rename this strain "Lavender Lullaby". I'd been unable to sleep for days when I came into the Shop and picked it up. After a few tokes from Batman, my trusty bong, I felt the silvery arms of Lavender float me away on a fresh breeze. The aches in my skull faded, and the tension in my shoulders ceased. I wasn't sleepy, but extremely relaxed, like my soul had just had a bubble bath. When it was time for bed, I closed my eyes as I hit the pillow and floated off to dreamland, where I swear to god, I dreamt I was flying on a dragon.

I'm not promising you that if you smoke Sunset Super Shop's Lavender you'll be able to dream about flying dragons through clouds made of indigo diamonds, glittering in the cosmic rays, plunging through waterfalls in a far-off-landscape...but I'm not saying it won't happen, either.

Wonderfully riding near the center of the wave with this one...
 
She goes down really nice and cool, mon  --- a refreshing sort of eucalyptus/tropical taste. (Even if you're not a huge fan of the taste of bud, this one is worth trying.)

Going down, you feel her gathering you in a soft, but very heavy comforter, and pulling you down with her. The comforter is just heavy enough that you don't feel like fighting against her, to get loose. So you don't. As the comforter gets heavier, you accept that you'd actually rather just do nothing. So that's what you do; you take it. 

And it's in the micromoment after you accept that she's in charge -- then you are - then she is -- and that you're riding the  wave together -- you taste ecstasy. 

She is indeed Royal Af Queen. Your loveliness. I thank you.

Gradually blasting off now...
She also made me comfortably horny. Tantra-esque.

When I heard this was available I couldn't pass up the chance to try something new.  I lived in Burlington Vermont for awhile and had a wide range of strains at my disposal.  This one easily jumped into my top 5.  The smell is aromatic, fruity but not overwhelming.  The pull is harsh, but like so many have said before, it's a good harsh.  The kind of harsh that tells you it's going to work well.  The come on is unassuming and quick.  Two or three pulls later I found myself on my couch with my headphones on and Paper Diamond pulsing in my ears.  It's not a couch lock, but don't expect to run a marathon.  The stone is euphoric, mellow and happy.  For my tolerance level, the duration of the stone was much longer then expected.  If you have the means I highly recommend this beauty.  I am very interested to see how it reacts to some downhill snowboarding.

Kuuuusshhhhhh is just how this one makes you feel. Like sinking into a nice pillow.

I didn't have a strong feeling one way or the other for the smoke. (Although my vape broke and I had to use my little water pipe -- so I tasted a LOT more smoke than I usually do. I will review again when my beloved vape is back in action.)

But the high is very nice combination body/head high. A calmly centered high. The creative buzzing is there, but turned to low simmer so it's not always poking at you. The body is relaxed, but not couch-locked. You can do necessary stuff; but the high is not what I'd describe as "energizing." (I actually found it a pretty helpful space for writing.)

This one really feels like a 60/40 Indica dominant hybrid. But I understand it's full Indica. Mild but pure.  (Damn, I just reread those last two sentences -- I'm really starting to sound like a pothead).

It occurs to me this would be a good choice for a family dinner. You want to be high, but you don't want your grandparents to know you're high. On this, you feel nicely chilled -- but you're neither a zombie idiot with zero energy nor a super-charged, but unfocused thinking machine. 

I think you could be pretty much "just right" at the dinner table with P. Kush, i.e., a smiling, charming, occasionally witty dinner companion. Just what the grandparents (and parents!) want to see -- and you want to give. 

Its charm is that it is very relaxing, but its real gift can only be appreciated if you allow it in and don't fight it. Turn yourself over to the Kush (Platinum version, no less) and let him hold you down -- and then you must choose to let go. At that moment -- at the precise point where your need to push against is equaled by your acceptance of being pushed -- you realize right then -- that you are just where you ought to be.

P. Kush pushes you toward Nirvana -- but in the end it's up to you -- whether you touch it or not.

Cannabissearch.com Buzz Rating: Frostbite is has pungent flavors of skunk, hash, earth and pine with a slightly spicy exhale. It smells just how it tastes. This bud has average smoke expansion and hits within a few minutes. This Sativa-dominant strain is great for daytime as well as nighttime use.

Chimera gives us yet another amazing strain. Frostbite comes in buds that are so caked with stick tri-chromes it actually appears white. Sprouting up from this snow-covered base are thick, orange pistils that looks like trees jutting up out of a snowy forest in January. They smell of fruit, dank, hash and skunk. This is a favorite strain among patients with all types of medical issues and is fairly common at many dispensaries.

Ideally, this plant thrives in an indoor environment, although she does mediocre when cultivated outdoors. She tends to be a single-cola plant, although if she is provided adequate space, branching out can occur. A great strain for the Sea of Green technique, growers can expect to harvest between 2 and 3 pounds. Much to the delight of those who cultivate here, Frostbite tends to have such a large single cola during maturity that a stake is needed to prevent this beauty from collapsing under her own weight.

Great for aiding in a wide array of ailments suffered by patients, Frostbite is not only a potent, but a long-lasting Sativa-dominant hybrid. Patients typically experience a mellow, relaxing, yet upbeat mixture of a cerebral high and a pleasant body high. This can usually be found for between $50 and $55 per eighth at most clubs.

---> I received a high from Mango Kush from a joint and in fact, this was the first high quality or ''piff'', ''fire-flame'' etc. weed I've experienced. After my first hit, I felt this unusual feeling of something like a device from the Matrix crawling up my spine and drilling a hole into my cerebrum. I've never felt such unusual yet interesting effect. After concluding this session, I had to go outside to get into my vehicle. As soon as I stepped foot outside...everything felt different. My eyes got heavy and I knew something was off. I shook it off and entered the car.... As soon as I started driving, I knew that the effects where taking place....If I'm not mistaken, I remember having a high speed chase against the sun! It was ex tactic and extremely entertaining. I couldn't stop laughing. Also, when entering a building, I felt as if I were in a major scene of an action movie. As the affects wore off I did start to get a rush of paranoia...but my mother did end up with me in the car which sort of explains that feeling...All in all this was a good strain....made me laugh like no other....

---> Favorite strain so far.....I will never forget my experience with Jack Herer....After smoking this, I was fulfilled with energy...All my worries were put on hold and my mood was just uplifted. I was able to operate a vehicle with no problem. My realm of time was completely tweaked. The first 45 minutes of this high felt like 2 hours....time went so slow.....but I had an absolute blast. My friends and I blasted music and it felt as if we were in the ultimate surround sound 100000 Giga Watt recording studio or whatever you want to call it. While listening to the music, I turned to my friend and it seemed as if the sound was coming from his own mouth! It also enhanced my driving skills and made them much sharper! An absolute favorite strain! The high is just great and it just makes you have a great time. Definitely one to share. Downside was that I did have a pretty bad headache when the buzz wore off...possibly due to the sudden rush of energy...but still a great experience.

Master OG is some form of the cross Master Kush x OG Kush.  I got it from Greendaze in Danville, CA and it was some extremely awesome medicine. Headband is a WIDELY used name for the kush x sd lines with those recognizable kushy scents and awesome tastes - however headband is not 707 headband and I think sometimes the 707 is dropped on the label and people fail to realize the better headband is the 707.  Sometimes it is at the consumer's expense sometimes not, either way it is headband, but just saying...

I've had some amazing regular headband but 707 is on another level - if you wanna know about the differences in genetics do a google search - 707 has bigger buds and better trich. coverage because it used the BEST sour diesel (ECSD) and the premier og kush (#7). Either way headband is a winner, but if you want to truly feel the headband on your skull, seek out the 707.

This review is for Platinum Bubba Kush, which has a dark green and purple appearance. I purchased this flower at Green Crop Co-Op in San Diego. The bud is HEAVILY covered in trichomes even to the naked eye. As previously mentioned, the bud is dark green and purple with some beige hairs. The nugs are medium to large and are very impressive. Just as impressive as the look is the smell. This Kush is not nearly as spicy many of the others I've sampled, instead it leans towards a strong pine with hints of citruce. It is a pleasure to break these flowers apart and let the delicious aroma waft over you.

The high is not so much an archetypical heavy Indica. Instead, it leans more toward a clear headed and uplifting, even euphoric state. I felt very happy, content, and extremely relaxed but not lazy. This strain is amazing.

The resiny texture will attest to a decent THC level so you can plan on some serious couch lock.

I obtained this strain at 61eleven, San Diego's only drive through dispensary. It is an outdoor version that is locally grown here in San Diego.

The bud is dense yet spongy and is a light green with, flecks of dark green and brown hairs throughout. The nugs are medium sized and have a definite citrus and sandalwood scent mixed with very slight piney undertones.

The high hit me all at once and relaxing wasn't my first choice. I almost wanted to go for a walk, but it was too late so I played some music and really enjoyed it. Very strong heady high...

I am reviewing the outdoor version of this flower, obtained from 61eleven dispensary, the drive-thru collective in San Diego.

The appearance is a medium green with few visible brown/tan pistils. Trichome coverage to the naked eye is very light, but under a loupe they are more apparent. The smell is a prototypical earthy, spiced, kush-type smell. Smell-wise it is nowhere near as pungent as some of the indoor OG Kush I've had.

If I'm honest it doesn't have much "bag appeal" at all, but the "taste" and "effects" departments are where this bud REALLY shines. 

This specimen when smoked, has a robust, flavorful and smooth smoke. It finishes very clean with almost no aftertaste. It's quite honestly one of the best tasting Kush's I've sampled to date.

What this particular OG Kush lacks in "bag appeal" it makes up for big time in the effects department. First, it is an extremely uplifting high that could be compared to that of a Sativa, but without any paranoia or racing thoughts. The effects are always predictable, a happy enjoyable high that is long lasting without being too "couchy" or demotivating. It does finish with a pretty heavy burn out so I can't fully recommend it for a daytime smoke.

So my co-worker invites some of my friends and I over to his house one day. We all know he smokes weed like us, but we got quite the enjoyable surprise. He took us up to his "Smoking Room", showed us his collection of pipes and bongs (50+), and breaks out the ganja. He first shows us some Red Haze, followed by Purple Urkle, and finnaly; White Rhino. We chose the White Rhino not knowing that both of the other 2 selections had better ratings. Let me tell you; 7 is an understatement. It's a very strong strain that will glue your ass to the couch for hours on hours. This is not a strain to be driving on, or to be under the influence of in public. Overall, I give it an 8.

Been growing AK47 for over 2 years indoors. This has been a constant in my garden and I've had many strains come and go in the time I've been with AK47. This is a must for the novice grower. It vegs super fast, is very bug resilient and produces top quality bud consistently. The buds are big, soft and covered in crystal. All my customers insist I keep this available. With careful Mom selection you can even find one that flowers in 7 weeks. I harvest when trichomes are 50/50 amber to clear. Cloning this strain is super easy and faster then any other strain I have tried. Anyone who says this isn't a top notch strain obviously was given a sample of something else and was told it was AK.

Blueberry is too broad of a description for this strain, which deserves serious medical studies on its own. 

DJ Short seems to have more muscle-spasm reducing qualities, especially in glycerite form.  BC Blueberry offers more THC in the same genetics.  

Muscle spasms, irritable bowel syndrome, spastic colon, hand tremor and restless leg syndrome symptoms are handled better with Blueberry than any Rx I know of, but then, I'm not a MD.

If you're currently taking Requip or other addictive Dopamine Rx, ask *your* MD, (get legal), then try a few puffs (or dropper-fulls) of Blueberry before bed and see if you don't sleep better.  Donate to NORML if you do.

The bud is lush and covered with pistils. Ground up, SAGE has a nice clean spicy smell with faint hints of citrus rind. 

Steamroller:  The exhale is smooth yet feels heavy and dense in the mouth. Initial sensation develops in sinuses and temples,  moving slowly down to the base of the cranium, invoking a sensation of a very small weight placed on the head. 

Water Pipe:  The taste comes out much harsher yet gives a sweeter taste on the palette. Sensation more pronounced in the ears and side of head this time. The forehead and temples feel as though they are melting and slowly sliding down the face and jaw.

I found this strain very enjoyable. After a couple small bowls from my pipe vaporizer, I received quite the high. I didn't enjoy the taste too much but that could just be due to improper cure. It tasted very earthy and musty. The smell of the bud is slightly earthy with a sour undertone. There is a small amount of time before the high really kicks in. But after it kicks in you feel very happy, lazy, very relaxed and hungry. All food tastes fantastic with this high, and there is no lack of appetite. Becareful to not over eat like i did! After the climax of the high (about 1h 30m) you start to feel very sleepy and if you dont push through the tiredness you will find yourself knocked out. Overall 8.3

Time seems to slow down significantly in that my thoughts take less time than usual. I thought of The Doors of Perception by Aldous Huxley and understood what he had been explaining throughout the entire book.

If you work over the short memory experience there's a lot of room for profound ideas.

Sour Diesel has been my staple for almost 8 months at this time. Nothing else gives such a rush to the head without being debilitating. Perfect for taking the edge off (and putting a new edge in), whether listening to music or in social situations, but be warned: this strain is extremely potent. High doses can result in (not necessarily unpleasant) serious couch lock/nausea in users with low tolerance. At the other end of the spectrum, Sour Diesel can produce the most incredibly euphoric highs. No other strain I've tried serves as a better anxiolytic, and to me Sour D is THE benzo equivalent bud. Great pick-me-up for depressive episodes and panic attacks. As an aside, Blue Dream provides a more mellow, longer high (think of it as being "stretched"), and NYC Diesel seems to be more mellow and have less of a cerebral rush in comparison.

It even seems like there are 3 times as many trichromes as I'm used to seeing on meds! Well-matured crystals; mostly clear bulbous heads with several frosted heads resembling granulated sugar.

It's named "Three Times Crazy" because it is bred from Granddaddy Purple, Bubba Kush, and OG Kush, and you really can tell from the effect and the way it tastes. The smoke is medium-bodied, the exhale tastes like a very flavorful purple ("skittles" taste), but it also has that sour kushy taste from the OG. Wow!! The effect starts off on the upper-side (probably from the OG) and then plunges you down into a deep, heavy indica effect.

Sour Diesel is a nice strain. I've smoked my fair share of this stuff, and it definitely gets the job done when it comes to pain relief. The smell is very pungent and heavy, like a skunk with slight citrus undertones.  The smoke can be quite harsh at times, even for seasoned tokers. I find that this strain often leaves me nice and relaxed, and feeling content with everything. However, be careful about how much you smoke in one session. Smoke too much too fast, and you may become paranoid. It seems to have some pretty infamous cottonmouth to accompany its high, so make sure to have a drink on hand just in case. With Sour Diesel, I also find it easy to fall asleep after the high has pretty much worn off, as I often feel burnt out afterwards. 

All in all, this is a solid strain. I give it a 7 out of 10.

From the local dispensary here in beautiful humboldt county, HPRC. HPRC is known for growing indoor, all-organic cannabis, utilizing over 30 years of growing experience from the head grower.

For 20$ a half 1/8th this Green Crack really delivers. Amazing visual aspects in this bud. Light green leaves which are almost completely covered in white crystal, accented with a fair distribution of orange hair. The smell is my selling point with this strain. Before your nose even reaches the jar, your greeted with a wave of sweet/sour musk which is also very present in the taste when smoked. 

This bud (if flushed correctly) has an extremely smooth smoke despite it's sweet/sour aroma. The taste is very similar to the smell, with no lingering smokey aftertaste. The high is very cerebral, clouding and distracting thought. Tingling sensation is also present throughout body. Drowsiness was minimal (but was smoked during the afternoon). Laziness a little, but the drive to be active was most present. 

Overall, this bud always is very attractive among a line up. I say it would place pretty high on a top 15, it's an oldie but goodie. As always though, with any strain, quality really depends on the growing conditions.

Beware if you are a newbie!!!! I'm a newbie, smoked everyday back in the 70's, but havn't since 78 or so. This weed gave me an extremely euphoric, laugh my ass of high, but at a cost. I am prone to panic attacks, reason I quit smoking in 78. But, I have had sooo many panic attacks, I can usually deal with them, as I did with the Purple Kush High induced anxiety. I don't like body buzzing or any kind of vibration feeling, and this high felt like a 100 people were massaging me with electric hand masagers! Very, Very intense, but to allieviate this, I simply kept walking around which nulified the vibration feeling, and let the euphoric part of the high through which made it easier to deal with the panic type feelings that were lying just beneath the surface of the euphoric, laugh your ass off high. for a few hours, if I stopped walking, I would feel the vibration which smothered the high. What to do? Keep walking. As I said, been through so many panic attacks, never died, never had a medical problem during one, all in my head. I know this, and can deal with panic attacks, especially if someone I trust is with me. If you are a newbie, I would definitely have a friend, spouse (as I did) around when smoking this for the first time, especially if you are anxiety, and panic ridden as I am. Cold/hot shower, hot tub, walking, exercising, wil alliviate the buzzing, vibrating feeling, and let the high come through, and man, what a high it is!

This is my default strain lately.  It has a very potent but level effect from start to finish, and just tends to take the edge off of things enough so I can relax, enjoy, but still focus on whatever I am doing at the time. I am a casual smoker, so usually it's the weekend and I am doing things around the house, yard work, etc. I also like this one when I am going to hang out at a bar with friends because it allows me to be "present" and social.  Some other strains tend to make me check out too much for that.

I can also read some pretty heavy books while using Master Kush, which is nice since I am into all kinds of philosophical subjects. It's a good one for video games and movies since it doesn't tend to cause your mind to wander much like other strains do.

Medicinally speaking, I suffer from some hereditary depression and anxiety which I have mostly controlled without the use of any drugs at all, thanks to educating myself about the problem.  However, there are some days where I wake up and I get some depressive effects and I become quiet, irritable and unmotivated.  A small hit of Kush tends to alleviate this for me, and put me in a much better mood.  Even once the effect of the weed wares off, I seem to have shaken off the depression I had felt prior.
This is a great day-time strain. Regardless of the goofy name, the cough isn't that bad. The effect is uplifting and positive. It's a "social-strain" for sure.

Sour Diesel is one of the strains I enjoy when I want to 'check out' for a while.  One time I tried to smoke this just before heading out to do some yard work.  I needed to wind some new cord on my weed-eater and I ended up sitting on the ground on my driveway for about 30 minutes zoning out and then busting up laughing at myself when I realized there was no way in hell I was going to be able to focus on the task at hand. Later when I was lucid again, I wondered if any of my neighbors saw me.  I'm sure they did.

This is a great one for Sundays when I like to study existential and philosophical subjects.  It tends to take me out of my head and straight into the stratosphere, which is nice in a meditative, exploratory sense. This is the kind of weed that will let you stop and stare in wonder at something that might normally seem insignificant, such as tree or smoke coming from an incense stick.

I consider this strain, for my use, to be an antisocial weed if I am going to be around non-smokers who don't want to philosophize.  I simply have no desire to talk about moronic subjects when using Diesel.  I would much rather take a journey of the mind, or laugh uncontrollably.

This strain was a roller coaster ride for for me, but in a good way.  One minute I am lucid, having a good talk or laugh with my friends, the next I am completely checked out to another place, staring off into the distance, and my friends are trying to get my attention back.  This seems to go on throughout the ride on LA Confidential.

Not my favorite personally, but I have no complaints either.  I haven't used it much, so I may add more info later.

This strian I would classify as a "OG Hippy Strain". It has that old school style 70's stone that is very creative and also poseses a deep head trip type stone that will leave you well rested if you take it before you sleep. You will also get to finsh all of your artwork projects that you have partially started with this one. As for the plant itself, growing is very easy, just pot it with some really good soil and a good metal halide let it go and feed it a lot. You must trim out the inside and under the canopy extensivly if you are topping the plant. Topping with this strain I have found, twice is a great number and will produce a very fat crop. Topping is also advisable because this plant strain will max out your grow box if you let it veg for too long. If you plan to NOT top this plant then you will need to trim out bottoms of all lower branches and interior leaves and buds because this plant grows vertically for at least 3 weeks in the flowering stage of its life cycle and light penatration is minimal. Jack Herer will get tall if you veg enough under metal halide up to six to ten feet. You will get huge, very big single cola if not topped which are very impressive to have for show, although you will experience much bigger yeilds when the plant is topped and allowed to spread out a little. The best benifit that I get personally is that it controls my back pain which was negated and also my neck pain also. This is a very very good strain for pain relief and also good for the beginner growers but you ussually will have to pay a pretty penny, for the price of these seeds are commonly up in the top brackets.

This is probably the best strain of weed I've ever smoked in my life. It provides an awesome Indica-style couchlock with amazing euphoria and an extremely wild headspace. It also has a distinct, almost minty taste that reminds me of its impressive high.
I love Platinum Kush.

Not too strong, but it gets the job done. It's very crystallized and feels sticky, even though it doesn't live up to what it looks like. The stuff also has an interesting flavor that actually, no-joke reminds me of Hawaii. Otherwise, Maui Waui is a generic sativa.
Purple Nepal is a great late-night sleep med with few negatives for that purpose.  Daytime use will slow you down a bit.  Also good for muscle tension.
God's Gift should be tried by any medical MJ patient dealing with stress.  General muscle relaxation, pain relief and emotional calming.

I wasn't a fan of the name, as I despise Bono and I can't stand how popular his terrible goodguy-badge-wearing band is, but I overcame that because the photos on the website and the description made it all too tempting to try.

A little different from my usual tastes of indicas that are dense and lightly sweet-tasting, but I enjoy this flavor immensely because of it's delicious kushy taste and very strong effect. On a scale of 1 to 10, with 10 being borderline opium, I would rate U2 Kush at a solid 9. It's excellent, I recommend it.

The name reminds me of that line in Pineapple Express: "Hands down, dopest dope I ever smoked. Dopest dope I ever smoked." I am a die-hard indica enthusiast, and this 80% sativa hybrid took me on a wonderful journey and taught me that not all sativas have to feel like straight-up crack. Indica relieves my anxiety, wheras sativa typically exacerbates it-- though not with Super Dope!

The name "Super Dope" even holds true at a microscopic level: the trichromes don't have space between each other like they usually do on buds, they're bunched close together and look like they exploded in every direction. Talk about a sticky bomb!! The nugs are truly the DENSEST I have ever seen in my life; the dispensary owner joked that I'd need a razorblade to cut them because the grinder won't work.

The taste is unique: it has that familiar lemon flavor that you get from sativas, but it also has an overwhelming minty quality to it as well... it almost tastes like a toothpaste. The high is equally unique; as this flavor contains 24% THC, it definitely gives euphoria and an uplifting sensation that's mellow and not intense. Though I still can't understand how, it's surprisingly heavy for how alert the effects are. Excellent for depression! Try it, and you won't be disappointed.

It has that stinky, cheesy, musty, dank smell, like Ingrid or UK Cheese.

My microscope inspection revealed plenty of gorgeous, matured trichromes that were either perfectly clear or hazy and sugary-looking. EXCELLENT for anxiety, and I have no doubt that it will help me sleep incredibly well tonight.

The smell and taste are phenomenal; somewhat citrusy. These are the kinds of nugs that microsopes were made for, as the surface is covered with thick, dramatic trichromes bursting from every direction with lots of big, gooey heads. Flawless.

The effect is great! I'm very sensitive to sativas and generally avoid hybrids, but this is SUPER heavy with a slight lift-- again, not in the hybrid sort of way, if it makes any sense. I guess one way of describing it would be a mega-downer weed with a hint of the smilies thrown in.

A strain that's been trademarked has a lot of hype to live up to, but I was very impressed. The buds are super purple-- cartoonishly purple-- and covered in frosty trichromes and bright orange hairs. The smell has a light sweetness, and the taste is sweet, smooth, and easy to take.

The effect is very heavy- like a perfect indica; it practically melts your stress and anxiety away. Soothing, relaxing, and great for pain relief. This bud is seriously PHENOMENAL. It's a modern medical miracle. Take my advice: go out of your way to try it.

Though the name of this flavor is somewhat girly and, well, childish, this flower is anything but. 

She truly is beautiful. Majestic shades of violent throughout the buds, with a very light scent that's sweet and citrusy. The taste is incredibly light, but the effect is very strong. Super mellow, soothing, relaxing feeling... the kind of indica that really helps unclench uptight muscles from a long day of work as well as relax your mind.

The first hour the after medicating I was motivated to do a little house work while maintaining a nice stony feel.  During this time I had no back pain or joint pain. The second hour brought on a more lethargic feeling with munchies.  It didn't make me tired at all though,  just a bit of couch lock.  The first half gave me a good mix of Indica/Sativa effects with a stronger Sativa feeling.  Second hour is when the Indica characteristics came through, not as clear headed in hour 2

Strain: Violator Kush 
["Indica" (Could be an Indica-dominant Hybrid* )]

Dispensary: Captiol Hill Patient Group

Donation: $15/gram.

Smell: A pine-like, light, herb-garden smell. It reminded me of rosemary or lavender.

Looks: Dry, darker green with midtone orange hairs and a fine layer of crystals/trichomes. 

Taste: The taste wasn't overpowering and actually quite smooth/light. There was an aftertaste of weed, which wasn't necessarily a bad thing.

Method of Ingestion: Vapor Balloon, followed with a Joint.

Toker's Tolerance: Med-High. Daily Vapor-user.

Buzz Type: A strong body high that relieved any muscle tension I had at the time. I was able to function at about 40% productivity (compared to a sober 80%), but found spelling and writing harder than normal. But, I was able to focus on reading and felt ambitious, it aided with an excellent high for researching/surfing the web.

About an hour and a half later, I was suddenly sober. The comedown either didn't exist or was unnoticable as I ended up being, 'Hey. Where'd my high go?'. All of the pain relief that had come with the high, disappeared. It was fairly disappointing.

So, I rolled up and smoked a quick J. After this, the relief returned and the Kush effect kicked in. Life slowed down. I got tired. After working on some artwork, I ended up laying in bed and playing online games. I could have passed out if wanted, but didn't have to.

Buzz Length: 1.5 - 2 hours top. 

Overall: I would classify the buzz as a hybrid with a strong, but very short body high. The sudden nature of the comedown was off-putting. The suggested donation price is too much for this strain. It is not worth 15$/gram, I would be more comfortable donating like 10$/gram as a fair price. The reason why the price is higher is due to the fact that it is a "local favorite".

Suggested For: This is a good strain if you have somewhere to be in 4-5 hours and want to relax your muscles, do research or surf the web before you head out. If you smoke enough of it, it'd be good for a nap.

*  When I was looking for pictures of this strain online, I found there has been discussion on whether this strain is truly an indica or just a hybrid-kush. This question comes with good reason, while there are kush-like qualities after smoking enough, the short timeline and the ability to be productive makes it questionable. There was no couchlock at all. I even went to the market down the street because I wanted some orange soda. Now, if I was smoking a pure, heavy indica, I'd be drinking water and pretending it was orange soda because I'm too relaxed to get dressed and go out in the rain for a soda. I was told it was Indica.

I tried looking up the genetics on this strain, and the info is very muddled. Apparently there is a Purple Dragon clone only strain going around the west coast which is Blue Dragon x Purple Urkle, and then there is another Purple Dragon strain coming out of somewhere in Canada which include genetics from Dutch Dragon, Purple Haze, and BC bud. 























   I picked up 1g from Relief Choices of Warren (not East Lansing, which is the only one listed on this site) in Michigan. They listed it as an indica. There is no purple to be seen in the bud, but it was a very healthy bright green and dense bud. The high is a definite creeper. It's like a plane taking off, at first you feel the rush of the acceleration but once at altitude, you feel a certain calm about it.  I see great potential in this type of high, but I need to adjust to it a bit.  Normally you feel a sort of body high with a bit of mental mixed into it....Lambs Bread goes straight to the dome in a hurry which makes it feel very powerful.  This aint no sitting weed.

This is Great for exploration. Definitely makes me feel stupid quickly, but also euphoric and easygoing, so I am totally comfortable even around family members while high on Jack Herer. The awesome boost in creativity makes up for the reduction in logic-based brainpower, so I actually feel just as quick-witted, and functional as I do sober, (which admittedly isn't saying much). As a classic sativa, I've found that the best thing to do while high on jack is to walk around outside, or just sit and think. It is not the best weed for enjoying mindless things, like watching TV. In fact, if I smoke this weed and then neglect to explore my imagination, I usually get antsy, and even anxious. Jack Herer may not have completely lived up to my expectations because of the relatively short time that the primary buzz lasts. The first time I got a quarter of this stuff was right after buying some great Sour D from the same dealer, and I was hoping for the same sort of thing. While the creative boost is similar to that of sour, I felt that diesel was more powerful, and long lasting. If i want to get super blazed, and really let go for the day, I'd smoke Sour Diesel, whereas Jack Herer is easy to use multiple times in a day and still manage my responsibilities.

The sample I had was of somewhat mid-level quality, although the overall smoke, taste, and high were still quite pleasant.

Right out of the bag, my sample had a heavy skunky smell. The buds were fairly light and fluffy on the outside but fairly dense on the inside. Long, spindly stems.

The leafy bits of the bottom of the bag didn't taste that fantastic, but upon breaking up a bud I was rewarded with a pleasant (although spicy almost) taste upon exhaling. The sample was great bong weed, and it only took a small bud to make a fairly potent one-paper joint.

The high is functional although it is somewhat relaxing and lazy. Useful for rainy days to relieve pain and for when relaxing with a book. When smoked in small amounts, the sample proved to be more of an up and heady/trippy high, whereas when smoked in larger amounts (such as larger joints) it proved to be much more of a body/relaxed high.

The come down isn't too bad, although I do consider this to be more of a night time weed as it is nice to sleep after coming down off of it. If used in the daytime in larger amounts, a nap or some caffeine may be in order.

Overall not the best sample ever, although I feel like the strain itself is good as I have tried another mid-level sample of it some time ago and it was enjoyable.

Ahh Dream Queen -- delivered to my High Life sided by the heavyweight Mango Trainwreck and the giggly newcomer, Querkle. 

Colored overwhelmingly in the light green hue of famous images of weed, it has spots of truly green leaves, a fair mass of hairy orange patches, but no purple dank. Nonetheless, trichome coverage is superb.

The first smoke out of a bowl leaves a slight semi-frosty layer on the middle of the tongue (or maybe that's just from some scooby snacks?), has that slight herbal/floral undertone, and is seriously hard to light because of the stickiness. Further hits were not particularly harsh or tasty, just the regular ol' 'errb...

But this is not any "regular ol' 'errb" whatsoever. As my toking companion so accurately remarked, "It feels like I'm drunk -- except without feeling bad in the stomach or head." It's certainly very buzz-y. Dream Queen, however, bestows upon you the gift of "fluidity": it seems as if walking is breathing, you seem to automatically do it and slide with it without thinking about it. 

After dreaming for additional 30 minutes, the Queen's high slowly begins to enter her descent -- a very focused, semi-tingly, pain-negating, and "functionally high" come down from the hustle and bustle of the I-just-smoked-this-shit-and-am-now-ridiculously-high period. This lasts about 30 more minutes....

And in the final 20 minutes or so, Dream Queen begins her final descent and actually lands so smoothly that you wake up at the gate, without ever really feeling like you got on the plane. 

This is some seriously dank bud.

Sour D has been one of my favorite strains since I first  began smoking. Because of that, it is literally my model for a good sativa, with a quality of high that truly sets the standard.

The bud is predominantly light green, with some light brown hairs visible. Its scent reminds me of sappy wood. The smoke was very smooth- I was able to singlehandedly roach the entire joint to nothing without a single cough (possibly due to the craftsmanship of the particular grower).

The strain leaves me clear-headed, giggly, and awestruck, almost reminding me of the onset from stronger psychedelics. Aside from a slight tremor of the body, the effects are 100% mental. This is the only strain that has ever given me true closed eye visuals and full blown mental imagery. I felt almost disconnected from my body, and my pain was very well managed.

I suggest this for: Pain, depression, or spiritual use.

I can't recommend it to lightweights, or for multitasking, as it can often result in a "+++" experience. Don't drive.

Dr. Grinspoon from Barney's Coffeeshop (Amsterdam), also known as Quaze Haze from Grey Area (Amsterdam) is by far the strongest sativa out there, hands down. Its a strain that looks like no other, growns like a weeping willow, clocks in at over 25% THC, almost no CBD, and smells like extreme citrus bathroom cleaner. I'm a  migraine and IBS sufferer, but would NOT recommend Grinspoon for migraines - this strain is 100% motivation power, like caffeine with the shakes or stomach problems. The trip is intense and long. I once smoked a serious joint of this stuff before boarding my flight at Schipol and had inner eye trails while up in the sky - super psychadelic stuff. NOT advised (AT ALL) for people with anxiety problems, but likely great for people with glaucoma and blood vessel restrictions as it makes your heart pump like a healthy oil rig. Expensive, hard to grow (18 - 22 weeks flower) but mighty worthy of the strongest sativa claim.

TOP-SHELF

This is another one of the house strains you can pick up at Highland Health, and easily a contender with Super Silver Haze for my favorite strain they grow. However this strain is nothing like the SSH. This is a stoney, hit you right between the eyes type of smoke. The flush is very good/perfect about 80% of the time (there has been maybe 3 times out of the MANY purchases of this strain that the flush was less then perfect, but still better then many flowers I have come across), burning to a very light gray ash.  The very first hit is by far my favorite, especially when I smoke this out of my Roor or in a Joint, those are by far the two methods of consumption that I feel make this strain shine. Anyways, back to what that first hit is like, it's goes straight to your dome, with thick chemy smoke that fills your lungs, and a high that rushes straight to your eyes. Coughing almost always occurs. The high continues to build into a very strong "stone" amazing body relaxation, and any daily aches and pains are memories at the moment. The intense head high is shorter lived and peaks around 40 mins, the body high and general sense of relaxation lasts much longer, generally close to 2 hours. As always the cure is the only place this bud is lacking, and keeping it from getting an 10/10, the buds are always dried, so it's not like your getting wet bud, but simply drying your flower properly is not the same as proper CURING, but as that is the only complaint I can come up with when thinking of my dear OG Chem Dawg it's hard to be too upset.

As a side note, this stuff is CRAZY STICKY. Maybe it was just the way it was cured, but I could barely grind this. Grinding this stuff should be a move in the P90X program.

This is one of the most famous strains of marijuana and with good reason. I normally smoke hybrid strains, and this was my first full Indica. It did not disappoint. I had only ever experienced head highs, and this was the first body high I'd ever gotten. Quite pleasant. Perhaps it was because I only took one hit (I like to do a review for each time I smoke, increasing the hits by 1 every time) but I was less than thrilled. The high was not bad by any means, but it was just not what I had expected from something so famous. It also may have been the drying of the buds and the degradation of THC. Unfortunately, thats what you have t deal with when you can't get it medically. Taking peoples words that it is the strain they say and that whomever grew it grew, dried, cured and stored it properly. Overall I'm not going to call it yet, I'll have to smoke it a few more times before I can get an official opinion. A nice body high and it let me sleep like a baby when I wanted to. A wonderful strain for insomnia, but more of a night cap strain, not so much a party type.

This is the second strain I've smoked that I've really enjoyed. It took three hits, but after three hits I was nice and toasty! I found that I was very talkative (in fact I could not shut up!) and I was also very giggly (I was laughing my ass off). I had a nice body high, although in the beginning it felt like my brain was vibrating. I had a nice head buzz that wasn't couch locking. It's definitely a social strain, I loved hanging out with my boyfriend and friend, and we had a lot of fun with it. I actually ate a lot before I smoked so I was nice and full when I started and (maybe that's why) I didn't really experience any of the extreme munchies other people mentioned in their reviews. WARNING: This strain makes you VERY talkative. As in you might not want to smoke this strain with someone you don't know because you WILL tell everyone your life story including secrets you probably don't want them to know.
Fucking awesome. Casual.

Taste is nothing to brag about, but it smells fantastic!

At a Grateful Dead show at Deer Creek Amphitheatre, joebrand (aka wonkanobe) and pbud met chemdog and sold him an ounce of very high quality pot for $500. joe and chemdog exchanged numbers and they later arranged for two ounces to be shipped to chemdog on the east coast. According to chemdog, one ounce was seedless and the other had 13 seeds.

In 91, chemdog popped the first 4 seeds. From these seeds, one male was found and disposed of (chemdog was young, you cant blame him). The 3 females were labeled chemdawg (now 91 chemdawg), chemdawg a (now chemdawgs sister), and chemdawg b. In 01, chemdog and his girlfriend attempted to germ 3 more seeds, labeled c, d, and e. the e seed never germinated, c turned out to be junk (according to chemdog), and chemdawg d was the keeper. In 06, chemdog and joebrand reunited and joe was given 4 of the last 6 beans: Chemdawg phenos 1-4, 4 being the chosen keeper. Joe thought the 4 was the best representation of the original and thus dubbed it the reunion pheno. Chemdog still has two seeds left in his stash.

Dr Grinspoon is named in honor of a hero, the brilliant cannabis advocate, researcher and author Dr. Lester Grinspoon. It's genetics is a pure heirloom Sativa. The plant grows thin and tall, and needs a longer flowering time around 95-100 days.  When mature, the colas look like compact, green and red-brown beads, loosely strung on thin stems with a dusting of THC crystals. The fragrance off the buds is of sumac and lemon and the smoke is light and tangy with citrus and tropical fruit aromas. Dr Grinspoon can stretch very tall indoors.  You can harvest these cannabis seeds outdoors in Mid November.  Dr. Grinspoon has a very high THC of 25% so it offers a strong, long-lasting, energetic and cerebral high. Old school Sativa of the highest order.

Jorge's Diamond is a unique resin-packed indica-dominant strain that is potent, sweet, flavorful and incredibly smooth smoking. The rare indica-dominant genes are mixed with just the right amount of sativa to give the smoke a very strong soaring long-lasting high. The exceptional taste and aroma are fruity and sweet. The insatiable taste is sweet and similar to wild honey smothered in raspberries. The strain is almost maintenance free, also spider mites and other pests know to leave Jorge's Diamonds #1 alone. Medical note: By Thin Layer Chromatography the THC percentage was calculated at 16 to 18%, while the strain (medical note) is high in THCV, CBD and CBN.

THC: 16-18%

Just picked up some pure og today and looked up some more info: 
Pure OG strain is a classic OG with a fresh fuel-like smell, smooth smoke, and great OG flavor. Pure OG is a San Fernando Valley (SFV) OG Kush F4 IBL (inbred line).

An IBL is a genetically homogeneous strain that grows uniformly from seed. When you cross two different IBL strains for the first time, it is called the F1 generation. When you cross two of the same F1 hybrid (inbreed), it is called the F2 generation. The process of selective inbreeding must continue at least until the F4 to stabilize the recurrently selected traits. When you cross two specimens of an IBL variety, you get more of the same, because an IBL is homozygous, or true breeding for particular traits.

Pure OG generally creates a body high that is relaxing and medicinal. Pure OG has higher CBD than THC equals a much heavier, sleepy type of high, that is good for a variety of medical problems.

This weed is perfect for late-night friendly conversations in a veranda, with a bit of Kraftwerk or Belle and Sebastian.

All I have to say is WOW!! HerbalMatch.org is the S***! Ryan is an awesome person to have a chat with, while remaining professional and discrete at all times. This was my first meeting with Ryan @ HerbalMatch.org, so I wanted to write a complete and accurate review so I apologize for the length.

I had spoke with Ryan a few time before coming to my house and he was a complete professional throughout the whole entire process. I was still a little cautious and weary about the whole delivery service as any responsible patient should be. So to ease my anxiety I had smoked a little bit before to calm my stress. I was feeling a little awkward due to being medicated, but Ryan was SUPER NICE / FUNNY and made me feel at ease. I'm sure he could tell that I was medicated, but he treated me with such class that I had totally relaxed. So far I was loving this guy! The best part is that he came to my house ABSOLUTELY FOR FREE!! With the price of gas soaring, I thought that was pretty cool. 

Since there were not any pictures I was a little hesitant to setup a meeting to purchase a half ounce. Ryan expressed his acknowledgement for my concerns. When he arrived we chatted while he let me sample each and EVERY strain that he carries in the comfort of my own living room!!!!! It was like going to Baskin Robbins!! It was THE BEST THING EVER!! I believe that all dispensaries/collectives should allow you to sample anything before you make a purchase! I ended up going the the KEN'S GDP which was dense, frosty, and very potent. I would give the bud a rating of 9/10 for taste 9/10 for appearance 9/10 price. My man Ryan is an innovator and a person who cares about his patients. I would like to consider myself a cannabis connoisseur and someone who is knowledgeable in many aspects of the cannabis community. With that said I was pleasantly surprised when Ryan was able to show me a battery operated portable vaporizer that I had never ever seen before. If you love cannabis and want to be WOW'd then HerbalMatch.org is definitely the place for you. I'm happy to say it is my new place when I want a hassle free transaction with no lines/crowds.

However, he did not only meet me for free, he also gave me a free pre-roll (valued @ $10) which I first wasn't overfilled with joy about because I have already been through the whole pre-roll gimmick with tons of dispensaries in the past. The 5 for $20 deal or 2 for $10 etc. the list goes on and on... Most of the time they are filled with s***y weed or shake. So you can now understand my reasoning for being a little hesitant of the pre-roll campaign. When I saw the pre-roll's it gave me more hope because they were pre-packaged from a vendor (Americone). I have smoked pre-roll's from vendors like this before, but for twice the money and they were definitely not worth the money, but I had NEVER tried this company before so what could I lose at least it was FREE right?! Because I had previously spoken with Ryan many times before our visit, he knew that I was a HUGE indica fan. So he had brought at least 15-20 different strains in pre-roll's for me to choose from. I ended up picking the Blackberry Kush which sounded delicious. When I decided to smoke my first Americone pre-roll I ripped the sealed package open and first took a whiff. I was kinda disappointed to be honest. The smell was definitely not what I had imagined, but I decided to give it a shot anyway. I was EXTREMELY surprised!! It was the smoothest pre-roll I had ever smoked. It burned like a cigarette without any runs and even had a pleasant minty taste to it. To make it even better it was definitely strong and potent. I was satisfied. I have paid for pre-roll of this quality for $20 each and these are only $10 TAX INCLUDED & DELIVERED!! Sign me up cause I will be back every week FOR SURE!

Dutch Treat #5 that is floating around the West Coast started it's path from B.C. seed breeder Jordan of the Islands.  A Master grower in Bellingham WA. brought the seeds over to the US and grew all 10 of them.  Word has it that these were some "special" behind the counter seeds that were offered to make up for a previous bad purchase several months before that wasted the growers time. Out of the 10 seeds that were labeled, the #5 plant was cloned (why you see it labeled DT #5) and sent out to the local growers in Bellingham that passed it around to "close" friends.  Today it is all over the West Coast including Maui and seems to be growing in popularity due to its heavy yields, easy trimming and rapid growth.  Because it is a relatively new strain (4 Years), clubs that have acquired this strain for sale can't seem to keep it in stock as customers often go on a waiting list to get it.   

There is some confusion as to it's name since there are other older versions of "Dutch Treat" that don't look anything like the #5, nor compare in quality.  For this reason, some people have called it Dutch Crunch instead.  

As to it's crosses, you would have to contact Jordan of the Islands to really get the detailed truth. Seed companies that sell the seeds still classify it as a "short and stalky" plant, but as any experienced grower would tell you, this plant is WAY OUT OF CONTROL, viney, lanky, extremely fast growing and sometimes falls over even before it starts budding.  Anyone trying to grow this plant, be ready to tie her down hard and use supports.   Many classify Dutch Treat as a heavy Indica punch you in the face High, yet the leaves on the plant are very much Sativa, very skinny, and harvesting goes to at least 8-9 weeks, sometimes more.

ok, first off im writing this review for several strains i guess, cause i wasnt smoking lemon kush exclusively, so i guess this is a little walk through of my experience...

first in the night, around 730 or so, i took a fairly nice rip of some blue dream that i have. about 2 hours later, i took another fairly large hit of J-1 (jack herer crossed with something else... forgot what its called) and about an hour after that i took a pretty large hit of lemon kush... about half a gram worth or so. thats when it hit me... holy shit so heres where my story begins... first id like to cap off that (im assuming) in large doses lemon kush is seriously really trippy. i never felt like this or experienced this before with marijuana alone, but ill explain that... ok-

so first off almost instantly (about 5 mins after i hit it) i felt as if i was spinning vertically. i wasnt dizzy, but i felt like i was suspended in air doing flips. i then got a really groovy wavy feeling with a nice body tingle. sometimes when my body tingles it feels very small in size, like pin needles, but painless of course, but the point of tingling are usually that size.. in this case it felt more like nails. it was super relaxing, and as i was watching the tv there was stardust around the tv screen. (stardust is my term for the multi-colored glow that appears around bright things in the dark, usually screens cause it looks like distorted rainbow glittery stuff that shimmers... stardust. woot!) this is pretty typical if im high enough. it was similar to Demerol and vicoden with a crazy thc high thrown in. i started to get hungry about 30 minutes later, so like traditionally do when im gonna make something i take another hit... this one was just as big as the last. wow, ok this is where it get trippy... my head was totally tripping out, similar to LSD (lysergic acid, not the marijuana strain) in the way that your mind works and thinks. you cannot control your thoughts, you just have to ride them out and enjoy it. im not saying i was hallucinating like LSD, cause i wasnt, im saying my thoughts were similar to that while under the influence of LSD. (im eating at this point btw)... soon thereafter it was as if i was an observer looking in at my thoughts. past dreams and experiences from long long ago were resurfacing and i was feeling them and watching them (with my minds eye) unfold before me. they only lasted about 1 minute, but felt like i had been living in each one of those thoughts for an hour or so. i went through about 10-15 'psycho-visions' until i eventually put on some solar fields (movements) and zoned out. it was one of the most intense psychological experiences i have ever had. i just find it really bizzare cause ive never had that happen to me while smoking marijuana alone. needless to say, it was friggin awesome! was definitely a positive self explorational experience. 

but like how i started this review, i posted the other strains that i smoked before i hit this, so i cannot say that it was just the lemon kush, but i smoked about the double the lemon kush than the other two combined. i smoked A LOT of the lemon kush at once, but as we all know mixing strains can produce drastically different results, but hey, it doesnt hurt to experiment. 

happy smokin!

This was my first medical marijuana purchase after I got my recommendation. I'm reviewing it a bit late, but hey, whatever. I went right over to THC Care Provider after my appointment, and was anxious to try some Fucking Incredible since you get a free gram your first visit, and I had EXACTLY $33 on me, and saw that they had 1/8s of Black Widow for that price. I had heard good things about it, so I figured I'd try it. When I got there, Mike took me back and showed me all the (VERY BEAUTIFUL) strains. I told him what I wanted, and he told me that Black Widow was LAST week's special, and that the current special was Super Skunk. However, luckily, they were out of Super Skunk, so he gave me the Widow at the discounted price! (Thanks for that!). Let me just say, I wish I had taken pictures when I first got it. It was the blackest, most crystalline bud I have EVER seen, and they give you big cuttings, not little dried up buds. I've been making the widow last, usually mixing it with other strains, for good reason. ANYTIME I smoke Black Widow, I'm guaranteed to be happy, carefree, and pain-free for the next few hours. It is by far my overall favorite strain, and well worth paying full price for.
