I'm a kinda small girl and I'm glad I could only hit a bowl of this. I split a fat nug with my friend and I was confused at first, because I had heard that Green Crack was so dank but I wasn't getting it. So I got through my bowl kind of unimpressed. THEN, my face around my eyes started to tingle and my face muscles felt lazy, my eyelids drooped, and I reached for my friend's bong again. The last thing I remember is saying 'just one more hit!'. I thought I passed out for 45 minutes, but when I looked at my phone only 2 had passed. I woke up panicked because I thought I might have done something I can't remember, or gotten myself in trouble, or wandered somewhere. I had that disoriented panic that lasted maybe 5 seconds, but that was 4 minutes to me. I didn't control my body too well, and the weight of my limbs and molasses in my brain and sense of loopy detachment convinced me I was in a lucid dream. I called my friend to comfort myself. She thought I was absolutely insane, because I was saying 'I was thiiiiiiinking, hehehehehe....okay, I was thinkingggggg that hehehehhHahahahahahaha okay, maybe I'm in a dreeeaam right now and I'm not annooooooying you with my pot talk in hehehehehehhe in REAL LIFE.' 
It was hard to understand my legs...it felt like I was on wheels that lagged behind my brain instructions. It was like being a baby. I had to relearn walking. We smoked on top of a hill...getting down without breaking my face was easy. I just told my brain 'get me down without hurting me.' and he did that. I recognized that I didn't know anything right then so I had to trust my brain to do what needed to be done. If I wanted to go faster, I told my brain 'speed up!' and the connection would be made in my leg wheels to turn faster. Then, I discovered my knees. I was overwhelmed with joy. I FOUND MY KNEES. I GOT IT GUYS. I HAVE FUCKING KNEES. THAT'S HOW THIS SHIT WORKS!!!
I was just consumed with my knees and their discovery. KNEES. Those are the spokes in my leg wheels!!
I was able to walk down a street, but I was giggly and it was obvious I was stoned out of my tree. I knew not to jump in front of cars but f there was someone speeding or running a red light I don't know if I would have been able to utilize my sense of self-preservation. Which seems depressing in retrospect. 
I didn't have the munchies. I was just concerned that my high would last the rest of my life. I truly believed it would. I thought my lucid dream lalaland where I zoomed around on thigh wheels was forEVER. Time was torturously slow. 
I went to Pete's coffee. I had to dig out my money. My backpack was an infinite black pit. SHIT. I really wanted to look sober. I forgot the price of my tea four times. The coffee guy had to hold up
His fingers to mime the numbers before I understood him. 
I bought tickets for Green Lantern 3D, but if I had seen that I would have died. Bridesmaids is terrible. It is a really awful movie. You'd think stoned....no. Worse. The blond woman actress looks like the monster Grim Reaper of nightmare death. And then it's just stupid, all I remember is some 50 year old asshole grabbed the Gr Reaper's 50 year old tit and started rolling it around and time was folded like 20 times into itself and it was just so much longer and revolting than necessary. 
By now, I know life isn't a dream. No munchies. I had to force myself to eat an apple to bring me down a bit so that I could function.
I blacked out a lot...which was weird and unanticipated. My conversation was slow and disjointed. I tried to talk fast to compensate because I knew I was high. Didn't work. Time didn't work. Two minutes felt like 20. 
I wasn't euphoric or in bliss. Just vaguely relaxed and detached. I took a break from myself. I thought I didn't like Green Crack. Looking back...I'm nuts for that shit. Can't wait till I can get my fingers on more. 
NOT FOR BEGINNERS OR LIGHTWEIGHTS OR ME PROBABLY but fuck that. I snickered for 15 minutes that my movie was at 4.20.
I know this is long, but I like the stories. Sorry guys. Have a bowl on me.
